    <node id="Meniscal Tear">
      <data key="d0">Meniscal Tear</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Meniscal Tear

A meniscal tear is a structural injury of the meniscus, the cartilaginous tissue of the knee joint. This condition is characterized by a tear or rupture within the meniscal tissue and is typically demonstrated and identified through magnetic resonance imaging (MRI). MRI imaging serves as the primary diagnostic tool for detecting and visualizing meniscal tears in affected patients, allowing clinicians to assess the extent and nature of the structural damage to the meniscus. The tear represents a disruption in the integrity of this important knee structure, which plays a crucial role in load distribution and joint stability.</data>
