    <node id="Musculoskeletal System">
      <data key="d0">Musculoskeletal System</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b6969a3f3abe42a30b2b43bfafceacaa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc908789d613380f6cd7ce177b5dfafb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91f2e17beb9f3d24b9faa9059ed6acae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5ef4a9ff207d5fcf312fa4948419500&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f3968a1e0f64443d559f9c75594cad0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5da01a385b47958d437c2b60db9a3505&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ff99b3fbcf99c238b4ecf7d0e0a7afc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47645b674af4f2a88a64e49657a83073&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1de22df34c77d7bc601fa40ded28a01&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a667de4da28bb439da82a6fd3153ca1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-858effb6f3bd62fa4b2171b7a13e1257&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1367d2b19d4c80169f6e3f681823cd2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e78b4d015419c364789de541e7d7c770&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c89e4f390f742775decbbc049992e1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a10d7b819d49867b6e7814e98a516ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e6cfcb84271ca620400ff56bfc7cd22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68e7577c18cbc865ebf744daec101377&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3303df334fce5c6456df7e61e6203291&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c623dc26c99ebd3a6caf0a7b69babb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43ac57a7d8c6d0fe3f3c2007ee0bfd6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8a8e6a29e85b55ab54a20a5f904ef16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-996a573759ff4451282c4bad9069e599&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7c81af782e89b002c04a944dc0cea584&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86ab66027f34b355354509e6cc65735e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22ab2cc7fede189ebd9f80f76a17ce09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-931d7f0d4f1634c02440df1aacdef13c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-606a0358ec61458bc198d5e4d438844f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d745ec6e17e6c423c81b61841434f2ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0cb44df10264318173904dd8b4a1b9e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c717ae7fe86b3a6ae2271e48ba22e47</data>
      <data key="d2">The Musculoskeletal System is the body system affected in the documented clinical case under examination. This anatomical system encompasses bones, joints, muscles, connective tissues, and related soft tissues that work together to provide structure, support, and movement to the body. The musculoskeletal system comprises interconnected components that function as an integrated physiological unit.

In the clinical case presented, the musculoskeletal system demonstrated comprehensive systemic involvement with notable pathological features affecting multiple anatomical regions. The condition was classified as high severity according to case documentation, reflecting significant clinical impact and extent of pathological changes. Multiple anatomical sites were affected, including the shoulder joint and its associated tissues (particularly the rotator cuff), the knee joint and related structures, and the spine. Clinical manifestations included shoulder stiffness and pain, as well as pain and swelling in the joints more broadly. The widespread nature of this involvement, spanning the shoulder, knee, spine, and associated connective tissues, underscores the systemic nature of the underlying pathology affecting this body system and the patient's overall clinical presentation.&lt;SEP&gt;The body system affected in the clinical case, encompassing bones, joints, muscles, and connective tissues.</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
