    <node id="Ataxia">
      <data key="d0">Ataxia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Ataxia is a neurological symptom characterized by the loss of coordination and balance control. This condition manifests as an inability to coordinate muscle movements effectively, resulting in incoordination of voluntary movements. Ataxia presents as a primary neurological symptom affecting the patient's coordination and balance, which may be observed upon clinical presentation or admission. In some cases, ataxia may present alongside other neurological symptoms, such as severe headache, indicating potential underlying complications or concurrent conditions requiring comprehensive clinical evaluation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-571ddc4aa63fdf4b9d03942b5048b279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a34ac93aa94bca40ac3bced0aa9de86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e52b6e535af5d46b5f2606e7f3ba818&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-903baf97d86d9b7dd49873c2407977ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbc516b53c71727bd08346a19ee50251&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd187f61bb50ddf67fed66dbf47414b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d94401800c111b74bf53e07ee0975662&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3b72ae1dccac058d727442c28727b3d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
