    <node id="Papilloedema">
      <data key="d0">Papilloedema</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A clinical sign revealed during neurological examination indicating optic disc swelling.&lt;SEP&gt;A clinical finding revealed on neurological examination indicating swelling of the optic disc.&lt;SEP&gt;Swelling of the optic disc observed during neurological examination of the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A clinical finding of swelling of the optic disc observed during neurological examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Optic disc swelling detected during neurological examination of the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A clinical finding identified during neurological examination, indicating increased intracranial pressure.&lt;SEP&gt;Papilloedema is a swelling of the optic disc caused by increased intracranial pressure.</data>
