      <data key="d0">Cerebellar Signs</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Clinical indicators of cerebellar dysfunction detected during neurological examination of the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;Neurological indicators of cerebellar dysfunction observed during examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Neurological signs indicating cerebellar dysfunction identified during examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Cerebellar signs are neurological indicators of cerebellar dysfunction, observed in the patient's examination.&lt;SEP&gt;Neurological findings indicating cerebellar dysfunction, detected during examination.</data>
