    </node>
    <node id="MRI Brain">
      <data key="d0">MRI Brain</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">MRI Brain is a non-invasive neuroimaging diagnostic technique that employs Magnetic Resonance Imaging to visualize internal brain structures and detect various pathological changes. The technique produces detailed, high-resolution images of the brain that enable clinicians to identify and evaluate abnormalities across a wide spectrum of neurological conditions.

MRI Brain serves as a primary diagnostic tool for detecting multiple types of brain pathology. The imaging modality can reveal ring-enhancing lesions within brain tissue, which may indicate infectious, inflammatory, or neoplastic processes. MRI Brain is particularly valuable for identifying acute territorial infarcts in the distribution of the middle cerebral artery (MCA), allowing for rapid assessment in acute stroke cases. The technique demonstrates high sensitivity in detecting haemorrhagic transformation, which is clinically significant in evaluating complications following ischemic events and guiding subsequent clinical management decisions.

Beyond acute vascular pathology, MRI Brain is utilized to identify diffuse leptomeningeal enhancement, a finding that may suggest meningitis, carcinomatous involvement, or other inflammatory conditions affecting the meningeal layers. The technique's sensitivity to various tissue contrasts and its ability to differentiate between different types of brain lesions make it particularly valuable for comprehensive neurological assessment and identification of intracranial abnormalities.

Overall, MRI Brain functions as a versatile and essential diagnostic imaging modality that provides critical information for clinical evaluation and management of diverse neurological conditions, ranging from acute cerebrovascular events such as ischemic infarction and haemorrhagic complications to infectious and inflammatory brain abnormalities. Its non-invasive nature and detailed imaging capabilities make it an indispensable tool in modern neurological diagnosis and patient care.&lt;SEP&gt;Magnetic resonance imaging of the brain used to detect haemorrhagic transformation in the patient.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-571ddc4aa63fdf4b9d03942b5048b279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b06c6a57e949da38959e52335f1e7ad5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ce7467c36645566972e9f92c5fea2ee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-163a075cd3f1260ecb6825df91ee03e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3052227d42277d8826362c90a01ca5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1911d102d00d5197ec74e282f36fbad9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a34ac93aa94bca40ac3bced0aa9de86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4fd7d8854cca43bc54c0fae9bacd07a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d21fe1428431fa9900c5bdf9740d3490&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4881dc7c4d5f1079552b2430a7677765&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e95a6830eba771de7657ec415c1a31b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e52b6e535af5d46b5f2606e7f3ba818&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-903baf97d86d9b7dd49873c2407977ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba602c293552d3d1cc227f2fb935fe2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6d9ce3f21c7d4f0447f68d282ddba6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-035214426d6755454aa9eb73b6e0d4e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbc516b53c71727bd08346a19ee50251&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd187f61bb50ddf67fed66dbf47414b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df174d639a33c9effb2f0ce6df80ce71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c15b0cde6ec5d9e10908aa2ac3619ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0808ea5951fe6ba96ffa3ee735cda17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-84e342b229c6a006856ecdc1a267768a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f26c6d54ddb9d4b1f92d2f09061da7f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66d79432cfb5da18b1aac0a6d772e676&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3cde4a56707d1854488f0b25ff33596&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d94401800c111b74bf53e07ee0975662&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b934702b442931687944c3b680751df6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2747605a19dd90cae3b9e6a20d1194f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1405b111c59c1691a48901cde2eed51b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3b72ae1dccac058d727442c28727b3d</data>
