    <node id="IV Ceftriaxone">
      <data key="d0">IV Ceftriaxone</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">IV Ceftriaxone is an intravenous antibiotic medication administered as a component of a patient's treatment regimen. This medication is specifically utilized in therapeutic contexts where bacterial infections require systemic antibiotic intervention through intravenous administration. The drug is integrated into comprehensive treatment protocols and may be employed for conditions such as meningitis, where intravenous delivery ensures adequate therapeutic levels and rapid systemic distribution to combat serious infections.&lt;SEP&gt;Intravenous antibiotic medication administered as part of treatment regimen.&lt;SEP&gt;Intravenous antibiotic medication administered as treatment for the patient's condition.&lt;SEP&gt;Antibiotic medication administered intravenously as part of treatment for the patient's condition.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-571ddc4aa63fdf4b9d03942b5048b279&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a34ac93aa94bca40ac3bced0aa9de86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4fd7d8854cca43bc54c0fae9bacd07a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d21fe1428431fa9900c5bdf9740d3490&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba602c293552d3d1cc227f2fb935fe2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbc516b53c71727bd08346a19ee50251&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0808ea5951fe6ba96ffa3ee735cda17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-84e342b229c6a006856ecdc1a267768a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66d79432cfb5da18b1aac0a6d772e676&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3cde4a56707d1854488f0b25ff33596&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d94401800c111b74bf53e07ee0975662</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
