      <data key="d2">CA19-9 is a tumor marker that was found to be elevated in the patient's laboratory results.&lt;SEP&gt;CA19-9 is a tumor marker that was elevated in the patient's laboratory results, indicating potential malignancy.&lt;SEP&gt;A tumor marker found to be elevated in the patient's laboratory results, indicating potential malignancy.&lt;SEP&gt;A tumor marker found to be elevated in laboratory results.&lt;SEP&gt;A tumor marker that showed elevated levels in the patient's laboratory results.&lt;SEP&gt;A tumor marker with elevated levels detected in the patient's laboratory results.&lt;SEP&gt;A tumor marker found to be elevated in the patient's laboratory results.</data>
