    <node id="Endoscopy">
      <data key="d0">Endoscopy</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Endoscopy is a versatile diagnostic procedure employed to visualize and examine internal organs and anatomical structures throughout the gastrointestinal tract. It functions as a direct diagnostic tool that enables clinicians to obtain critical diagnostic information necessary for patient management and treatment planning.

Endoscopy demonstrates significant diagnostic capabilities across multiple regions of the gastrointestinal system. In esophageal examinations, the procedure can visualize the esophagus and identify various pathological conditions. These include Barrett's esophagus with high-grade dysplasia, a precancerous condition characterized by abnormal cellular changes in the esophageal lining. The procedure has also successfully identified esophageal varices grade III, which are enlarged veins in the esophagus that pose a significant risk of bleeding. Additionally, endoscopy has revealed ulcerating masses located at the gastroesophageal junction, indicating the presence of malignant or erosive lesions at the junction between the stomach and esophagus.

Beyond esophageal applications, endoscopy has been utilized to visualize the colon, where it has successfully identified multiple polyps—abnormal tissue growths that may have malignant potential and require further evaluation or removal. The procedure can examine different regions of the gastrointestinal tract and identify a wide range of pathological conditions spanning from precancerous changes and benign growths to vascular abnormalities and malignant lesions.

By enabling direct visualization of affected areas, endoscopy provides essential diagnostic information that supports clinical decision-making and guides appropriate therapeutic interventions. The procedure remains a fundamental tool in gastrointestinal medicine for comprehensive examination and diagnosis of patient conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;A diagnostic imaging procedure performed to visualize the gastrointestinal tract.&lt;SEP&gt;A diagnostic procedure used to visualize the esophagus and identify Barrett's oesophagus with dysplasia.&lt;SEP&gt;Diagnostic procedure used to visualize the oesophagus and identify varices.&lt;SEP&gt;A diagnostic procedure performed to visualize the gastro-oesophageal junction and identify the ulcerating mass.&lt;SEP&gt;A diagnostic procedure performed to visualize the gastrointestinal tract, revealing an ulcerating mass at the gastro-oesophageal junction.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-913dac86f1445586ee7313cee3abcef4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed0783f447cb66336d0ee665a9a9ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17baf644d96495d064f9649f631230b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0cf79a93d6937f4e196efd0a76b1c14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed28d4753317331d50864a0ff241202a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-552541f5707dbc91dc2b39f24da42ff3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359c4bdb901dcb37d2cf0fa307a2c571&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0848622c01d4f566da1895987417746&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-299e0d28d253c37f9dddf4aef8eb2c94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5efbbabff30dce7757a05e1d7b57eaa2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93f288f93598c3b3a931faed20b2314c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4fb8802354fa5826fc6a61e1d4703650&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6540caa7beb945f0321bf38942587d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42c5dd7e4b8ae3efca148f8d10f468da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7dfbf9ae7bdd2da18160509a98a29b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32a4845ff65651415af840aed5ad1767&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aea77867f87b397c2569ebf2e109e550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d50fc57a8c14c7819b2950816abc682&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa60f44fc47125398c7ec53a5186865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af3da83b586005637f4530b60892346&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12b0793fd5ff30936be7578fadb2f11c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-389cb396bf4e6268fa31af66e862032b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93cc887c0186b2515e2821eabf31639d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-735be7666813a3f1eedf039a72df5db3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17ee3298badd5c634297742f3bfdd8e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd08cbda0f2618e783e7d18b1e718420&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bd68a770018591cf0e4611e9e14ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b832bffca6f5b953e97047ac37cd38ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1693a9d96722a090fabd3e1bd2ba20a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbdb6e100fb2bdb409feb08c479fa265&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d99b348010e0859bf79ca469b926378b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f78e14c615a6efcb86bacdcef718021&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-304f340ad4cf36f85eadeea2200b5890&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1375b9b5b2e11625f9232d34b4107e38</data>
