    <node id="Oesophageal Adenocarcinoma">
      <data key="d0">Oesophageal Adenocarcinoma</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Oesophageal adenocarcinoma is a malignant tumor of the oesophagus that has been established as the primary diagnosis. This condition represents a glandular origin cancer affecting the lower esophagus. The disease is characterized as a primary malignancy of the esophageal tissue, constituting the confirmed final diagnosis for the affected patient.&lt;SEP&gt;The primary diagnosis of cancer of the esophagus in the patient.</data>
