    <node id="Systemic Lupus Erythematosus">
      <data key="d0">Systemic Lupus Erythematosus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Systemic Lupus Erythematosus (SLE) is an autoimmune disease that has been diagnosed in the patient. This condition is characterized by systemic inflammation affecting multiple body systems and is confirmed through both clinical presentation and laboratory findings.

The diagnosis of Systemic Lupus Erythematosus is supported by specific immunological markers. Key laboratory findings include positive antinuclear antibody (ANA) results and elevated anti-double-stranded DNA (anti-dsDNA) levels, which are diagnostic hallmarks of the disease. These abnormal laboratory results, combined with the patient's clinical presentation, provide the basis for the diagnosis.

The condition manifests through inflammatory symptoms distributed across multiple organ systems in the body. The diagnosis was established through a comprehensive evaluation incorporating clinical findings, laboratory test results, and imaging studies. As the underlying autoimmune condition in this patient, Systemic Lupus Erythematosus represents a complex disease process requiring careful clinical and laboratory assessment for confirmation.&lt;SEP&gt;An autoimmune disease diagnosed in the patient, characterized by ANA positive and anti-dsDNA elevated blood test results.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-010177962773e82b3b10b0765421d512&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1367d2b19d4c80169f6e3f681823cd2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e78b4d015419c364789de541e7d7c770&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68e7577c18cbc865ebf744daec101377&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3303df334fce5c6456df7e61e6203291&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c623dc26c99ebd3a6caf0a7b69babb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43ac57a7d8c6d0fe3f3c2007ee0bfd6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c8a8e6a29e85b55ab54a20a5f904ef16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22ab2cc7fede189ebd9f80f76a17ce09</data>
