    <node id="Synovitis">
      <data key="d0">Synovitis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Synovitis is the inflammation of the synovial membrane, which is the tissue lining that surrounds and lubricates the joints. This condition has been identified and documented through magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) findings across multiple anatomical locations in affected patients.

The synovitis identified in various clinical cases involves inflammation of the synovial membrane in several key joint regions. These include the knee joint, wrist joint, metacarpophalangeal joints (the knuckle joints connecting the hand to the fingers), and the shoulder joint. In each case, MRI imaging has been instrumental in detecting and demonstrating the presence and extent of synovial inflammation.

The consistent use of MRI as a diagnostic tool across all documented cases highlights the importance of advanced imaging techniques in identifying synovitis, as MRI provides detailed visualization of soft tissue structures, including the synovial membrane, making it a reliable modality for confirming inflammatory changes within affected joints. The presence of synovitis across multiple joint regions suggests either a systemic condition affecting various joints or localized inflammatory responses specific to each affected area.&lt;SEP&gt;Inflammation of synovial tissue identified on MRI imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;Inflammation of the synovial membrane in the knee, demonstrated by MRI imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;Inflammation of the synovial membrane identified on MRI imaging.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-010177962773e82b3b10b0765421d512&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc908789d613380f6cd7ce177b5dfafb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f3968a1e0f64443d559f9c75594cad0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05e39d703a228f9f75806162f2ec5ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47645b674af4f2a88a64e49657a83073&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-858effb6f3bd62fa4b2171b7a13e1257&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1367d2b19d4c80169f6e3f681823cd2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a10d7b819d49867b6e7814e98a516ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c623dc26c99ebd3a6caf0a7b69babb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57d53deb985a155d9d6cc2e16d224de8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-931d7f0d4f1634c02440df1aacdef13c</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775168550</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bone Marrow Oedema">
      <data key="d0">Bone Marrow Oedema</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Bone Marrow Oedema is a pathological condition characterized by fluid accumulation and swelling within the bone marrow tissue. This condition is consistently identified and demonstrated through MRI imaging, which serves as the primary diagnostic modality for detection and visualization of bone marrow involvement.

Bone Marrow Oedema can affect multiple joints throughout the body, with documented presentations in the knee, shoulder, and other affected joints. The condition manifests as fluid accumulation within the bone marrow space, which appears as swelling on MRI imaging studies. This pathological finding indicates inflammatory changes occurring within the affected joints and represents bone involvement in the underlying disease process. The oedema reflects the patient's broader pathological presentation, demonstrating systemic or localized inflammatory activity that extends beyond soft tissue to involve the bone marrow compartment itself.

The detection of Bone Marrow Oedema on MRI is clinically significant, as it serves as an imaging biomarker for disease activity and inflammatory burden in affected joints. The presence of this finding contributes to comprehensive assessment of joint pathology and helps clinicians understand the extent of disease involvement in the skeletal structures.&lt;SEP&gt;Swelling in bone marrow detected on MRI imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;Bone marrow edema in the knee, identified through MRI imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;Bone marrow swelling identified on MRI imaging of the spine.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-010177962773e82b3b10b0765421d512&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc908789d613380f6cd7ce177b5dfafb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f3968a1e0f64443d559f9c75594cad0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05e39d703a228f9f75806162f2ec5ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47645b674af4f2a88a64e49657a83073&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-858effb6f3bd62fa4b2171b7a13e1257&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1367d2b19d4c80169f6e3f681823cd2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a10d7b819d49867b6e7814e98a516ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c623dc26c99ebd3a6caf0a7b69babb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57d53deb985a155d9d6cc2e16d224de8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-931d7f0d4f1634c02440df1aacdef13c</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
