    <node id="Lung Adenocarcinoma">
      <data key="d0">Lung Adenocarcinoma</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Lung adenocarcinoma is a type of lung cancer that has been established as the primary diagnosis in the patient. This malignancy originates from glandular cells within the lung tissue and was confirmed through diagnostic imaging and clinical evaluation. The condition represents a malignant lung cancer characterized by adenocarcinoma histology, making it distinct from other lung cancer subtypes. The diagnosis of the patient's lung adenocarcinoma was established based on comprehensive clinical and imaging findings, providing the basis for the patient's primary oncological diagnosis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-556d7ea1921560596bb0c596a00bdf0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92cc2c46c1f49338ed7955ea4238e60f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11944cb5618b1905065e32d7424e5ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c41f1161752e203627b5fc920fca07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b29acdc1599ff32318f1144aaa062a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b74bdb93da896529bce41ee41924095c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e4a466aae7fe4bee947643e66e2ba9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ef20424effc0d32c39fcdcec5da83d2</data>
