    <node id="Bronchoscopy">
      <data key="d0">Bronchoscopy</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Bronchoscopy is an invasive diagnostic and endoscopic procedure that enables direct visualization of the airways and bronchi. It is performed to examine the mucosal surfaces of the respiratory tract, identify abnormalities, and assess the structural and functional integrity of the bronchial passages. Healthcare providers use bronchoscopy to evaluate patients with suspected or documented airway disease and to conduct comprehensive clinical assessment of airway pathology.

During bronchoscopy examinations, various findings may be observed depending on the patient's condition. The procedure can reveal normal mucosa, indicating a healthy respiratory tract with no apparent abnormalities. In cases of pathology, bronchoscopy can detect significant abnormalities including mucosal inflammation in the airways and the presence of purulent secretions, which may indicate infection or inflammatory processes within the respiratory tract. Additionally, bronchoscopy can identify endobronchial structural abnormalities, such as endobronchial tumors or other irregularities within the bronchial passages. These visualization capabilities make bronchoscopy a valuable diagnostic tool for comprehensive assessment of airway pathology and disease characterization, allowing clinicians to determine appropriate clinical management based on specific findings observed during the procedure.&lt;SEP&gt;Bronchoscopy is a diagnostic procedure that showed normal mucosa in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;Bronchoscopy is a diagnostic procedure performed on the patient that showed normal mucosa.&lt;SEP&gt;An endoscopic diagnostic procedure that showed purulent secretions in the patient's airways.&lt;SEP&gt;A diagnostic procedure that showed purulent secretions in the patient's airways.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-556d7ea1921560596bb0c596a00bdf0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-937e867ddae2f8daaa79bd2e639976eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cfa77dcd4a2e473aabe4108bc1732c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d29c25e21e325edd849f3dc97bf8a04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-348a6f93e1df4665db6794f8f475315a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5543cdd6c57fb9e70e4d6b2688e3521&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3758214300d6bd794534d0e32e9bd057&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92cc2c46c1f49338ed7955ea4238e60f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c35da8135a5d590d4accdb1b51d149c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf05a1180370ca5c22ffbfcdb89ab2d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7f38ad205281fc2b3d3fdc52c5a8b5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11944cb5618b1905065e32d7424e5ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c41f1161752e203627b5fc920fca07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74df9a5aaec0ab322e9634e2a357e4ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-680b0868e00cfb2dc1ba062d72742486&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d69e90de14f13f99bd017794598000f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b29acdc1599ff32318f1144aaa062a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50c06f071bd4436025fb35de50515fda&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b77bea8599e47e5947ec3a7be0ce9b73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b74bdb93da896529bce41ee41924095c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ac0d1d3c9697cf3ad1c05e8e52ee8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e4a466aae7fe4bee947643e66e2ba9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa76722cb250ebdc3971241f8d1d7a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ef20424effc0d32c39fcdcec5da83d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dda6359792d27d913bf9dbba5833f91f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c4cc1d83b1ff0beb41c0996e0bed59f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ebdec2fe609dbeb73244f6c370f4d8eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeb696350165bf9ae41216f5236c3817&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8ab7539afd48876f5bb300e184ed79b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a71fb455018aca9558b624f3b05ab137&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51e9f120ecce8be89d00fb7954cbe1a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c7f5f1efa9fe1ad162b412383e280bf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4f335b1b7bae18006bc038ab4128db1</data>
