    <node id="Pulmonary Function Tests">
      <data key="d0">Pulmonary Function Tests</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Pulmonary Function Tests are diagnostic assessments designed to measure lung capacity, airflow, and overall respiratory function. These procedures provide objective evaluations of breathing patterns and pulmonary performance, with spirometry serving as a key component of the testing methodology.

The Pulmonary Function Tests performed on this patient revealed a mixed pattern of respiratory dysfunction combining both obstructive and restrictive elements. The Forced Expiratory Volume in one second to Forced Vital Capacity ratio (FEV1/FVC) was measured at 0.58, which falls significantly below the normal threshold of 0.70 and indicates airway obstruction. This reduced ratio is consistent with impaired airflow during expiration and was documented consistently across multiple clinical assessments. In addition to the obstructive findings, the Pulmonary Function Tests also demonstrated restrictive components of respiratory impairment, suggesting reduced lung capacity alongside the airflow limitation.

This mixed presentation of respiratory dysfunction reflects complex pulmonary pathology encompassing both airway obstruction and diminished lung volume capacity. The diagnostic findings consistently demonstrate this combined pattern of lung function abnormality rather than isolated obstruction or restriction alone. The patient's respiratory dysfunction is multifactorial, requiring thorough clinical evaluation and comprehensive management strategies to address both components of the identified impairment.&lt;SEP&gt;Pulmonary function tests are diagnostic procedures that indicated normal spirometry.&lt;SEP&gt;Pulmonary function tests are diagnostic tests performed on the patient indicating normal spirometry.&lt;SEP&gt;Diagnostic tests that indicated a restrictive pattern in the patient's lung function.&lt;SEP&gt;Diagnostic tests that indicated a mixed pattern in the patient's lung function.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-556d7ea1921560596bb0c596a00bdf0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-937e867ddae2f8daaa79bd2e639976eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cfa77dcd4a2e473aabe4108bc1732c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d29c25e21e325edd849f3dc97bf8a04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-348a6f93e1df4665db6794f8f475315a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5543cdd6c57fb9e70e4d6b2688e3521&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3758214300d6bd794534d0e32e9bd057&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92cc2c46c1f49338ed7955ea4238e60f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c35da8135a5d590d4accdb1b51d149c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf05a1180370ca5c22ffbfcdb89ab2d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7f38ad205281fc2b3d3fdc52c5a8b5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11944cb5618b1905065e32d7424e5ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c41f1161752e203627b5fc920fca07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74df9a5aaec0ab322e9634e2a357e4ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-680b0868e00cfb2dc1ba062d72742486&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d69e90de14f13f99bd017794598000f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b29acdc1599ff32318f1144aaa062a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50c06f071bd4436025fb35de50515fda&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b77bea8599e47e5947ec3a7be0ce9b73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b74bdb93da896529bce41ee41924095c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ac0d1d3c9697cf3ad1c05e8e52ee8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e4a466aae7fe4bee947643e66e2ba9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa76722cb250ebdc3971241f8d1d7a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ef20424effc0d32c39fcdcec5da83d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dda6359792d27d913bf9dbba5833f91f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c4cc1d83b1ff0beb41c0996e0bed59f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ebdec2fe609dbeb73244f6c370f4d8eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeb696350165bf9ae41216f5236c3817&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8ab7539afd48876f5bb300e184ed79b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a71fb455018aca9558b624f3b05ab137&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51e9f120ecce8be89d00fb7954cbe1a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c7f5f1efa9fe1ad162b412383e280bf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4f335b1b7bae18006bc038ab4128db1</data>
