    <node id="FEV1/FVC Ratio">
      <data key="d0">FEV1/FVC Ratio</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">The FEV1/FVC ratio is a pulmonary function measurement that expresses the ratio of forced expiratory volume in one second (FEV1) to forced vital capacity (FVC). In the case presented, the FEV1/FVC ratio has a value of 0.58, which is consistently identified across all descriptions as indicative of obstructive airway disease or airway obstruction.

A ratio of 0.58 falls below the normal threshold (typically 0.70 or 70%), indicating that the patient experiences airflow obstruction. This measurement demonstrates an obstructive airway pattern, meaning that the patient's airways are narrowed or blocked, reducing the amount of air that can be forcefully exhaled in the first second of expiration relative to the total volume of air that can be exhaled. The FEV1/FVC ratio serves as a key diagnostic indicator in pulmonary function testing, helping clinicians identify and assess the severity of obstructive airway diseases such as chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) or asthma.&lt;SEP&gt;FEV1/FVC ratio of 0.58 is a pulmonary function measurement indicating airflow obstruction.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-556d7ea1921560596bb0c596a00bdf0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-937e867ddae2f8daaa79bd2e639976eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-348a6f93e1df4665db6794f8f475315a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5543cdd6c57fb9e70e4d6b2688e3521&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c35da8135a5d590d4accdb1b51d149c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-680b0868e00cfb2dc1ba062d72742486&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b74bdb93da896529bce41ee41924095c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ac0d1d3c9697cf3ad1c05e8e52ee8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ef20424effc0d32c39fcdcec5da83d2</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775168566</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Obstructive Pattern">
      <data key="d0">Obstructive Pattern</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic finding from pulmonary function tests showing airway obstruction with FEV1/FVC ratio of 0.58.&lt;SEP&gt;A pulmonary function test result indicating airflow limitation with FEV1/FVC ratio of 0.58.&lt;SEP&gt;A pulmonary function finding indicating airway obstruction with FEV1/FVC ratio of 0.58.&lt;SEP&gt;Abnormal pulmonary function test results indicating airway obstruction with reduced FEV1/FVC ratio.&lt;SEP&gt;Obstructive pattern is a pulmonary finding characterized by reduced airflow indicated by FEV1/FVC ratio of 0.58.&lt;SEP&gt;A pulmonary function test result showing airflow obstruction with FEV1/FVC ratio of 0.58.</data>
