    <node id="Right Upper Lobe Consolidation">
      <data key="d0">Right Upper Lobe Consolidation</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Right Upper Lobe Consolidation is a radiological finding detected on chest X-ray imaging that indicates abnormal density or consolidation in the right upper portion of the lung. This finding represents a pathological condition of the lung tissue in the upper right lobe, characterized by increased density compared to normal lung parenchyma. The consolidation may be associated with fluid accumulation or inflammatory processes affecting the right upper lobe. Right upper lobe consolidation serves as an important diagnostic indicator on chest imaging studies and typically suggests underlying lung pathology that requires clinical correlation and further evaluation to determine the specific etiology.&lt;SEP&gt;A finding on chest X-ray indicating consolidation in the right upper lobe of the patient's lungs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-937e867ddae2f8daaa79bd2e639976eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b29acdc1599ff32318f1144aaa062a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50c06f071bd4436025fb35de50515fda&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ac0d1d3c9697cf3ad1c05e8e52ee8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa76722cb250ebdc3971241f8d1d7a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ef20424effc0d32c39fcdcec5da83d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dda6359792d27d913bf9dbba5833f91f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeb696350165bf9ae41216f5236c3817&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8ab7539afd48876f5bb300e184ed79b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775168739</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pulmonary Embolism">
      <data key="d0">Pulmonary Embolism</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Pulmonary Embolism is the established primary diagnosis for the patient, characterized by the formation of a blood clot within the pulmonary arteries. This condition involves blockage of the pulmonary blood vessels, which prevents normal blood flow through the lungs. The diagnosis of Pulmonary Embolism was determined based on clinical findings and represents a serious cardiovascular condition requiring immediate medical intervention. The presence of this blood clot in the pulmonary arteries necessitates prompt anticoagulation therapy to prevent further complications and manage the patient's condition effectively.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-937e867ddae2f8daaa79bd2e639976eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7cfa77dcd4a2e473aabe4108bc1732c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3758214300d6bd794534d0e32e9bd057&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c35da8135a5d590d4accdb1b51d149c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7f38ad205281fc2b3d3fdc52c5a8b5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11ac0d1d3c9697cf3ad1c05e8e52ee8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa76722cb250ebdc3971241f8d1d7a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dda6359792d27d913bf9dbba5833f91f</data>
