    <node id="Hyperinflation">
      <data key="d0">Hyperinflation</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hyperinflation is a radiological finding observed on chest X-ray that indicates abnormal over-expansion or over-inflation of the lungs. This condition represents an excessive accumulation of air within the lungs, resulting in abnormal lung expansion beyond normal physiological limits. Hyperinflation appears as a characteristic finding on chest radiography and is used clinically to identify patients with compromised pulmonary function or obstruction.&lt;SEP&gt;Hyperinflation is a finding on chest X-ray indicating abnormal lung expansion in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A condition observed on chest X-ray indicating excessive air in the lungs.&lt;SEP&gt;A finding on chest X-ray indicating overinflation of the lungs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7cfa77dcd4a2e473aabe4108bc1732c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3758214300d6bd794534d0e32e9bd057&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c35da8135a5d590d4accdb1b51d149c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf05a1180370ca5c22ffbfcdb89ab2d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11944cb5618b1905065e32d7424e5ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b77bea8599e47e5947ec3a7be0ce9b73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e4a466aae7fe4bee947643e66e2ba9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a71fb455018aca9558b624f3b05ab137&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51e9f120ecce8be89d00fb7954cbe1a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c7f5f1efa9fe1ad162b412383e280bf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4f335b1b7bae18006bc038ab4128db1</data>
