    <node id="Night Sweats">
      <data key="d0">Night Sweats</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Night sweats are a clinical symptom characterized by episodes of excessive perspiration or sweating during sleep, reported by the patient as part of their medical presentation. This symptom has been documented alongside several other clinical manifestations, including dyspnoea, wheeze, and a productive cough. Night sweats are classified as a secondary symptom within the patient's overall clinical presentation.

The symptom is commonly associated with respiratory infections and represents an important component of the patient's reported symptomatology. Night sweats, in conjunction with the other presenting symptoms, contribute to the broader clinical picture requiring medical evaluation and assessment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-3d29c25e21e325edd849f3dc97bf8a04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5543cdd6c57fb9e70e4d6b2688e3521&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf05a1180370ca5c22ffbfcdb89ab2d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e4a466aae7fe4bee947643e66e2ba9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c4cc1d83b1ff0beb41c0996e0bed59f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a71fb455018aca9558b624f3b05ab137&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51e9f120ecce8be89d00fb7954cbe1a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4f335b1b7bae18006bc038ab4128db1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
