    <node id="Dysphasia">
      <data key="d0">Dysphasia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Dysphasia is a language disorder that affects a patient's ability to communicate through speech and language. This neurological condition impacts both the production and comprehension of speech, resulting in difficulties with verbal expression and understanding language. Dysphasia is typically identified and diagnosed during neurological examination, where healthcare professionals assess the patient's language abilities and communication skills. The disorder manifests as impaired speech production or comprehension, limiting the patient's capacity to effectively communicate their thoughts and understand others. As a language-based neurological symptom, dysphasia represents a significant disruption to normal linguistic functioning and communication abilities.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b06c6a57e949da38959e52335f1e7ad5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3052227d42277d8826362c90a01ca5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4881dc7c4d5f1079552b2430a7677765&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e95a6830eba771de7657ec415c1a31b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbc516b53c71727bd08346a19ee50251&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df174d639a33c9effb2f0ce6df80ce71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-84e342b229c6a006856ecdc1a267768a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f26c6d54ddb9d4b1f92d2f09061da7f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
