    <node id="Low Severity">
      <data key="d0">Low Severity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Low Severity is a severity classification assigned to clinical cases that indicates a lower degree of medical urgency and a low level of clinical concern. This classification serves as a standardized measure within clinical documentation systems to denote conditions that require medical attention but do not present immediate or critical clinical urgency.

Low Severity has been applied across multiple medical domains and system-specific conditions documented within clinical cases, including musculoskeletal system conditions, dermatological conditions, and gastrointestinal system disorders. When assigned to a clinical case, Low Severity represents a low-risk classification for the patient's condition, reflecting that while the condition warrants medical evaluation and monitoring, it does not constitute an emergency or critically urgent situation requiring immediate intervention.&lt;SEP&gt;The clinical case has been classified with low severity.&lt;SEP&gt;The severity level assigned to the clinical case on the date of 2025-04-15.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-dc908789d613380f6cd7ce177b5dfafb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0cf79a93d6937f4e196efd0a76b1c14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6832ceabd069924c459708223a28ba62&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f3968a1e0f64443d559f9c75594cad0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fefabc1e665ca1162ec747e9ecad131&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5efbbabff30dce7757a05e1d7b57eaa2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93f288f93598c3b3a931faed20b2314c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7dfbf9ae7bdd2da18160509a98a29b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d50fc57a8c14c7819b2950816abc682&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa60f44fc47125398c7ec53a5186865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af3da83b586005637f4530b60892346&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c60f4b4404d3d935bf9d0334c2044fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93cc887c0186b2515e2821eabf31639d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6d9ce3f21c7d4f0447f68d282ddba6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86ab66027f34b355354509e6cc65735e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66d79432cfb5da18b1aac0a6d772e676&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3cde4a56707d1854488f0b25ff33596</data>
