    <node id="Hepatocellular Carcinoma">
      <data key="d0">Hepatocellular Carcinoma</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hepatocellular Carcinoma is a primary liver cancer that originates in the liver tissue. It is confirmed through liver biopsy, a diagnostic procedure in which tissue samples are analyzed to definitively establish the presence of the disease in the patient. This type of cancer represents one of the most common forms of primary liver malignancy and is identified through pathological examination of biopsied tissue samples obtained from the affected liver.&lt;SEP&gt;A primary liver cancer confirmed by liver biopsy in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A malignant tumor of the liver confirmed through liver biopsy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed0783f447cb66336d0ee665a9a9ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17baf644d96495d064f9649f631230b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359c4bdb901dcb37d2cf0fa307a2c571&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3d50fc57a8c14c7819b2950816abc682&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa60f44fc47125398c7ec53a5186865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-389cb396bf4e6268fa31af66e862032b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b832bffca6f5b953e97047ac37cd38ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1693a9d96722a090fabd3e1bd2ba20a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d99b348010e0859bf79ca469b926378b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-304f340ad4cf36f85eadeea2200b5890</data>
