      <data key="d0">Primary Sclerosing Cholangitis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The diagnosed condition in the patient requiring specific medical management.&lt;SEP&gt;The diagnosed condition characterized by inflammation and scarring of bile ducts.&lt;SEP&gt;Primary sclerosing cholangitis is the confirmed diagnosis, a condition affecting the bile ducts.&lt;SEP&gt;Primary sclerosing cholangitis is the confirmed diagnosis indicating progressive inflammation and fibrosis of the bile ducts.&lt;SEP&gt;The confirmed diagnosis describing a chronic disease affecting the bile ducts.&lt;SEP&gt;The diagnosed condition characterized by inflammation and fibrosis of the bile ducts.</data>
