    <node id="Diuretics">
      <data key="d0">Diuretics</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Diuretics are a class of pharmaceutical agents prescribed as medications that form part of patient treatment regimens. These drugs are administered to manage various medical conditions, including decompensated heart failure and decompensated cirrhosis. In the context of cardiac conditions, diuretics function as key therapeutic agents within comprehensive treatment plans. The medications are commenced as part of structured treatment regimens tailored to individual patient needs, working alongside other interventions to address underlying pathophysiology and symptom management in patients with fluid overload and related complications.&lt;SEP&gt;Medications administered to the patient as part of treatment for hypertensive urgency.&lt;SEP&gt;Medication administered to the patient as treatment for acute NSTEMI.&lt;SEP&gt;A class of medications administered to the patient for cardiac management.&lt;SEP&gt;A medication class prescribed as part of the patient's corrective treatment plan.&lt;SEP&gt;Medication class administered to treat fluid overload associated with cardiac dysfunction.&lt;SEP&gt;Medications commenced as treatment for decompensated cirrhosis to manage fluid retention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed0783f447cb66336d0ee665a9a9ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17baf644d96495d064f9649f631230b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64cd049e5c5b89e54dfbde1ab8bbcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed28d4753317331d50864a0ff241202a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359c4bdb901dcb37d2cf0fa307a2c571&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9953fc82aa24f3592983321f1a24638a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6540caa7beb945f0321bf38942587d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af3da83b586005637f4530b60892346&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df3d0210bdc53243a466e464ecd7efc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-983b5f68059fc792b82433c7f0d17697&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da9725a3a120031d9b91eb87eeb7ea97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bd68a770018591cf0e4611e9e14ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4004490c7f995b8c84484a113ba933ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-304f340ad4cf36f85eadeea2200b5890</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169119</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Propranolol">
      <data key="d0">Propranolol</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Propranolol is a beta-blocker medication that has been initiated and prescribed as part of comprehensive patient treatment regimens. In clinical practice, propranolol serves multiple therapeutic purposes within structured treatment plans designed to address serious hepatic conditions.

Propranolol is specifically employed in the management of decompensated cirrhosis, a severe form of liver disease characterized by loss of hepatic synthetic function and clinical decompensation. Within this context, propranolol plays a critical role in managing portal hypertension, a major complication of advanced liver disease characterized by abnormally elevated pressure in the portal venous system. By reducing portal pressure through its beta-blocking effects on splanchnic vasculature, propranolol helps prevent serious complications such as variceal bleeding and other manifestations of portal hypertension.

As a beta-blocker, propranolol functions by antagonizing beta-adrenergic receptors, which results in decreased cardiac output and reduced splanchnic blood flow. This mechanism makes it particularly valuable in corrective and preventative treatment approaches for patients with cirrhosis and associated portal hypertension. Propranolol is typically commenced as part of a broader, multifaceted treatment regimen designed to stabilize the patient's condition and prevent disease progression or acute decompensation events.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed0783f447cb66336d0ee665a9a9ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17baf644d96495d064f9649f631230b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed28d4753317331d50864a0ff241202a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359c4bdb901dcb37d2cf0fa307a2c571&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6540caa7beb945f0321bf38942587d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af3da83b586005637f4530b60892346&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bd68a770018591cf0e4611e9e14ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-304f340ad4cf36f85eadeea2200b5890</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169124</data>
      <data key="d6" />
