    <node id="Dietary Sodium Restriction">
      <data key="d0">Dietary Sodium Restriction</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Dietary Sodium Restriction

Dietary sodium restriction is a non-pharmacological, therapeutic intervention implemented as a key component of patient management and treatment plans. This dietary intervention involves restricting sodium intake and is typically commenced as part of a corrective treatment approach to address specific clinical conditions.

Dietary sodium restriction is primarily employed in the management of decompensated cirrhosis and related complications such as fluid retention. By limiting sodium intake, this intervention helps to reduce fluid accumulation and supports the overall therapeutic goals in managing cirrhotic patients. The intervention functions as part of a comprehensive, multi-faceted management strategy that may incorporate both pharmacological and non-pharmacological approaches to optimize patient outcomes and clinical stability.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed0783f447cb66336d0ee665a9a9ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17baf644d96495d064f9649f631230b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed28d4753317331d50864a0ff241202a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359c4bdb901dcb37d2cf0fa307a2c571&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6540caa7beb945f0321bf38942587d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af3da83b586005637f4530b60892346&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bd68a770018591cf0e4611e9e14ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-304f340ad4cf36f85eadeea2200b5890</data>
