    <node id="Ankle Oedema">
      <data key="d0">Ankle Oedema</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Ankle Oedema is a clinical symptom characterized by swelling in the ankle region resulting from fluid retention. This condition was observed during the patient's physical examination and clinical presentation. The ankle swelling was present for a duration of 14 days at the time of presentation. Ankle oedema manifests as visible swelling in the ankles and serves as a clinical indicator of underlying fluid accumulation in the ankle tissues. The symptom was identified as a notable finding during the patient's initial assessment and physical examination.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-147130d60b546439813daa2cf522a31b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-590c301f3f3b6ed7e8dd79ff818eb970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc54586b6f383f8d77f096cecdbfabb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f98e594c48f4396c9da7f66fe58029d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1f1f43b5a8581949513cce1ff0ab8de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df3d0210bdc53243a466e464ecd7efc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af28652606d78849d0249d790f40681f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e434022f7935c8daeaf7caba8c447e9f</data>
