    <node id="QTc Prolongation">
      <data key="d0">QTc Prolongation</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">QTc Prolongation is an electrocardiographic finding characterized by an abnormally prolonged QTc interval, which represents the QT interval corrected for heart rate. This condition is demonstrated on a patient's electrocardiogram (ECG) and indicates an electrical conduction abnormality or electrical abnormality in the heart's cardiac electrical activity.

The QTc interval represents the duration of ventricular repolarization adjusted for the patient's heart rate. When prolonged beyond normal limits, QTc prolongation reflects an extended duration of the QT interval in the patient's cardiac electrical activity. This abnormal finding on ECG is clinically significant as it suggests impaired electrical conduction within the heart's ventricles, potentially increasing the risk of dangerous cardiac arrhythmias such as torsades de pointes.&lt;SEP&gt;Prolonged QT interval on electrocardiogram indicating cardiac electrical abnormality.&lt;SEP&gt;ECG finding indicating prolonged corrected QT interval on the patient's electrocardiogram.&lt;SEP&gt;An abnormal electrocardiogram finding indicating prolongation of the QT interval on the cardiac electrical activity.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-147130d60b546439813daa2cf522a31b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-590c301f3f3b6ed7e8dd79ff818eb970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a80dbd998d7aced4f85f4e332b3980&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a418de55ab776ed3382840643ce211c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24b0722d4e6a03efb1f886b8c96c34fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc54586b6f383f8d77f096cecdbfabb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48d485c49b8fecae90419b536e5c22d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b9466306ab7d2011082fa69d4835ba8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-983b5f68059fc792b82433c7f0d17697&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fa5295eee150f6d2e5bed021b15fafd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e434022f7935c8daeaf7caba8c447e9f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169055</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Altered Bowel Habit">
      <data key="d0">Altered Bowel Habit</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Altered Bowel Habit is a clinical symptom characterized by a change in normal bowel function patterns and movement characteristics. This gastrointestinal symptom is presented by patients experiencing various forms of gastrointestinal pathology and dysfunction. Altered Bowel Habit typically manifests as observable deviations from a patient's baseline bowel function, reflecting underlying gastrointestinal conditions.

Altered Bowel Habit frequently presents as part of a constellation of gastrointestinal symptoms. It is commonly associated with other clinical manifestations including rectal bleeding and jaundice. In documented cases, Altered Bowel Habit has been observed in conjunction with jaundice for extended periods, with some instances lasting approximately ten weeks. This symptom serves as an important clinical indicator of underlying gastrointestinal pathology, helping clinicians identify and assess the nature and severity of intestinal or digestive disorders in affected patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Altered bowel habit is a clinical symptom associated with the patient's condition.&lt;SEP&gt;A change in normal bowel function presented as a symptom by the patient alongside jaundice.&lt;SEP&gt;A symptom presented by the patient characterized by changes in normal bowel function, associated with rectal bleeding.&lt;SEP&gt;A change in bowel function associated with the patient's gastrointestinal condition.&lt;SEP&gt;A change in bowel patterns observed in the patient, associated with rectal bleeding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed0783f447cb66336d0ee665a9a9ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17baf644d96495d064f9649f631230b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e0cf79a93d6937f4e196efd0a76b1c14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-552541f5707dbc91dc2b39f24da42ff3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359c4bdb901dcb37d2cf0fa307a2c571&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0848622c01d4f566da1895987417746&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5efbbabff30dce7757a05e1d7b57eaa2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7dfbf9ae7bdd2da18160509a98a29b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32a4845ff65651415af840aed5ad1767&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aea77867f87b397c2569ebf2e109e550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd08cbda0f2618e783e7d18b1e718420&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b832bffca6f5b953e97047ac37cd38ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbdb6e100fb2bdb409feb08c479fa265</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775168888</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Anorexia">
      <data key="d0">Anorexia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Anorexia is a clinical symptom characterized by loss of appetite experienced by patients. It represents a reduction in the desire to eat and can manifest as a primary symptom or as an associated symptom within a broader clinical presentation.

Anorexia frequently appears alongside other gastrointestinal symptoms in patients. Notably, it is commonly presented in conjunction with jaundice and altered bowel habits, forming part of a constellation of gastrointestinal manifestations. The symptom is associated with various patient conditions and serves as an important component of the overall clinical assessment when evaluating gastrointestinal health.

As a clinical presentation, anorexia is directly reported by patients and documented as part of their symptomatology during medical evaluation. Its presence, particularly when combined with other gastrointestinal symptoms such as jaundice and changes in bowel function, can provide diagnostic insight into underlying patient conditions and requires appropriate clinical assessment and management.&lt;SEP&gt;Loss of appetite associated with the patient's clinical presentation.&lt;SEP&gt;Loss of appetite experienced by the patient as part of the clinical presentation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ed0783f447cb66336d0ee665a9a9ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6540caa7beb945f0321bf38942587d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7dfbf9ae7bdd2da18160509a98a29b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aea77867f87b397c2569ebf2e109e550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12b0793fd5ff30936be7578fadb2f11c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-389cb396bf4e6268fa31af66e862032b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bd68a770018591cf0e4611e9e14ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b832bffca6f5b953e97047ac37cd38ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f78e14c615a6efcb86bacdcef718021&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-304f340ad4cf36f85eadeea2200b5890</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169122</data>
      <data key="d6" />
