    <node id="Echocardiography">
      <data key="d0">Echocardiography</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Echocardiography is a non-invasive diagnostic ultrasound imaging procedure used to visualize the heart and comprehensively assess both cardiac structure and function. The technique enables real-time visualization of cardiac structures, allowing clinicians to examine anatomical features and evaluate physiological performance in patients with suspected or confirmed cardiac disease.

In clinical practice, echocardiography serves multiple diagnostic purposes and provides essential information that guides clinical decision-making and therapeutic planning. The procedure can identify various cardiac abnormalities and conditions affecting patient health. Specifically, echocardiography is employed to detect reduced ejection fraction, indicating impaired cardiac output and systolic dysfunction. Ejection fractions can be significantly reduced, with documented cases showing values as low as 35%, which represents severe cardiac dysfunction. The imaging technique is also utilized to identify regional wall motion abnormalities, which reflect localized areas of the myocardium that fail to contract normally and often suggest prior myocardial injury or ischemia. Additionally, echocardiography can reveal pericardial effusion, representing an abnormal accumulation of fluid within the pericardial sac surrounding the heart. The procedure further enables detection of valvular pathology, such as mitral regurgitation, which represents inadequate closure of the mitral valve leading to backward blood flow into the left atrium.

Through its comprehensive assessment capabilities, echocardiography simultaneously evaluates multiple cardiac parameters, including ventricular function, wall motion, valve integrity, and pericardial status. This multifaceted diagnostic capacity makes echocardiography a cornerstone imaging modality in cardiovascular medicine for assessing patient cardiac health and guiding subsequent therapeutic interventions.&lt;SEP&gt;Ultrasound imaging test of the heart performed to assess valve function and cardiac structure.&lt;SEP&gt;Imaging test performed on the patient that showed reduced ejection fraction of 35%.&lt;SEP&gt;An ultrasound imaging method used to visualize cardiac structures, revealing mitral regurgitation in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;Ultrasound imaging technique used to visualize the heart and detect pericardial effusion.&lt;SEP&gt;Imaging test that revealed mitral regurgitation in the patient's heart.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-147130d60b546439813daa2cf522a31b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a6870a0ae60e5e97ee38192a8c7cb33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-590c301f3f3b6ed7e8dd79ff818eb970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64cd049e5c5b89e54dfbde1ab8bbcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a80dbd998d7aced4f85f4e332b3980&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c23e378760ce2cf115e65e9075717448&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a418de55ab776ed3382840643ce211c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24b0722d4e6a03efb1f886b8c96c34fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc54586b6f383f8d77f096cecdbfabb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432f575b36f0861b9c262c0f7ea4613e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9953fc82aa24f3592983321f1a24638a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0260e68b82e6826effdbcc686dec9cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48d485c49b8fecae90419b536e5c22d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51b315cb721376514a08823422d5c30f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f98e594c48f4396c9da7f66fe58029d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1f1f43b5a8581949513cce1ff0ab8de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df3d0210bdc53243a466e464ecd7efc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b9466306ab7d2011082fa69d4835ba8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-983b5f68059fc792b82433c7f0d17697&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da9725a3a120031d9b91eb87eeb7ea97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af28652606d78849d0249d790f40681f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2571e07f042a9f93f2e47306fa03981&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4004490c7f995b8c84484a113ba933ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fa5295eee150f6d2e5bed021b15fafd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e434022f7935c8daeaf7caba8c447e9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15f9eef500fedf61aecc494b64b11664&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-205b75d592f5c35757c06b25aa8e1984</data>
