    <node id="Cardiac System">
      <data key="d0">Cardiac System</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The Cardiac System is the physiological system affected in the clinical case under examination, specifically involving the heart and cardiovascular function. This body system has been identified as the primary organ system involved in the patient's condition and is classified with critical severity status. The critical nature of the cardiac system involvement was documented as of October 15, 2025, indicating the urgent and serious nature of the patient's cardiac pathology requiring immediate clinical attention and intervention.&lt;SEP&gt;The physiological system affected in this clinical case involving the patient's heart and cardiovascular function.&lt;SEP&gt;The cardiac system is the physiological system affected in this clinical case, as indicated by the system classification.&lt;SEP&gt;The cardiac system is the body system affected in this clinical case, noted as the system type in the case documentation.&lt;SEP&gt;The body system affected in the patient's clinical case, indicated by the system classification.&lt;SEP&gt;The body system affected in this clinical case, as indicated by the system classification.&lt;SEP&gt;The cardiac system is the bodily system affected in this clinical case, responsible for heart function and circulation.</data>
