    <node id="Type 2 Diabetes">
      <data key="d0">Type 2 Diabetes</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Type 2 Diabetes is a chronic metabolic disorder that represents a significant component of patients' past medical histories. This endocrine condition is characterized by dysregulation of glucose metabolism and is classified as a chronic condition requiring ongoing management.

Type 2 Diabetes contributes substantially to overall patient health status and has important clinical implications. Notably, the condition influences cardiovascular risk, making it a significant factor in assessing patients' broader health profiles and disease burden. As a documented element of past medical history, Type 2 Diabetes serves as an important clinical consideration in understanding patient health trajectories and informing medical decision-making.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8a6870a0ae60e5e97ee38192a8c7cb33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-590c301f3f3b6ed7e8dd79ff818eb970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64cd049e5c5b89e54dfbde1ab8bbcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-24b0722d4e6a03efb1f886b8c96c34fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9953fc82aa24f3592983321f1a24638a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df3d0210bdc53243a466e464ecd7efc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2571e07f042a9f93f2e47306fa03981&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4004490c7f995b8c84484a113ba933ec</data>
