    <node id="ECG">
      <data key="d0">ECG</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Electrocardiography (ECG) is a non-invasive diagnostic method used to record and assess the electrical activity of the heart. ECG examinations detect various cardiac abnormalities by analyzing the heart's electrical patterns and are performed to evaluate a patient's cardiac status and identify potential cardiac conditions requiring clinical attention.

In the clinical context of this patient, ECG testing revealed multiple significant and concurrent cardiac abnormalities. The electrocardiograms demonstrated atrial fibrillation, a condition characterized by irregular heart rhythm. Additionally, the ECG findings indicated QTc prolongation, which represents an extended interval in the heart's electrical cycle and may indicate an increased risk for certain arrhythmias. The tests also detected left bundle branch block in the patient, a conduction abnormality affecting the heart's electrical system. Furthermore, the ECG demonstrated ST-elevation in leads II, III, and aVF, a pattern indicative of cardiac ischemia that suggests reduced blood flow to specific regions of the heart supplied by these leads.

These diverse and complex ECG findings collectively indicate that the patient experienced multiple concurrent cardiac abnormalities, each with distinct clinical implications. The combination of atrial fibrillation, QTc prolongation, left bundle branch block, and ST-elevation represents a serious cardiac condition requiring appropriate medical management based on the severity and nature of each identified abnormality. The comprehensive ECG evaluation provided essential diagnostic information necessary for determining the patient's cardiac status and guiding clinical decision-making.&lt;SEP&gt;Electrocardiogram test that demonstrated atrial fibrillation in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;Electrocardiogram test performed to diagnose cardiac rhythm abnormalities.&lt;SEP&gt;Electrocardiogram test performed on the patient that demonstrated QTc prolongation.&lt;SEP&gt;Electrocardiogram test used to detect atrial fibrillation in the patient.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8a6870a0ae60e5e97ee38192a8c7cb33&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-590c301f3f3b6ed7e8dd79ff818eb970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-64cd049e5c5b89e54dfbde1ab8bbcd95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-13a80dbd998d7aced4f85f4e332b3980&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c23e378760ce2cf115e65e9075717448&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a418de55ab776ed3382840643ce211c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-432f575b36f0861b9c262c0f7ea4613e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9953fc82aa24f3592983321f1a24638a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51b315cb721376514a08823422d5c30f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f98e594c48f4396c9da7f66fe58029d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a1f1f43b5a8581949513cce1ff0ab8de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df3d0210bdc53243a466e464ecd7efc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b9466306ab7d2011082fa69d4835ba8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-983b5f68059fc792b82433c7f0d17697&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da9725a3a120031d9b91eb87eeb7ea97&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af28652606d78849d0249d790f40681f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4004490c7f995b8c84484a113ba933ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fa5295eee150f6d2e5bed021b15fafd0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15f9eef500fedf61aecc494b64b11664</data>
