    <node id="Circumferential Colonic Thickening">
      <data key="d0">Circumferential Colonic Thickening</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Circumferential colonic thickening is an abnormal imaging finding detected on computed tomography (CT) abdomen examinations. It is characterized by abnormal thickening of the colon wall that extends around the entire circumference of the colon, affecting the structure in all directions. This finding represents a structural abnormality of the colon that can be definitively identified and visualized through CT abdomen imaging.

Circumferential colonic thickening is clinically significant as it may indicate underlying pathological conditions affecting the colon. The most common associations include potential malignancy of the colon or inflammatory diseases of the colon. When observed on imaging, this finding warrants further clinical investigation and evaluation to determine the underlying etiology and guide appropriate patient management and treatment decisions.&lt;SEP&gt;An abnormal finding on CT abdomen imaging showing thickening around the colon.&lt;SEP&gt;Circumferential thickening of the colon observed through CT abdomen imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;An abnormal finding on CT abdomen scan indicating potential malignancy in the colon.&lt;SEP&gt;Thickening of the colon wall that extends around the circumference, identified on CT imaging.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-17baf644d96495d064f9649f631230b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0848622c01d4f566da1895987417746&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-299e0d28d253c37f9dddf4aef8eb2c94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4fb8802354fa5826fc6a61e1d4703650&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7dfbf9ae7bdd2da18160509a98a29b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32a4845ff65651415af840aed5ad1767&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aea77867f87b397c2569ebf2e109e550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93cc887c0186b2515e2821eabf31639d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-735be7666813a3f1eedf039a72df5db3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17ee3298badd5c634297742f3bfdd8e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd08cbda0f2618e783e7d18b1e718420&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b832bffca6f5b953e97047ac37cd38ec</data>
