    <node id="Hypoalbuminaemia">
      <data key="d0">Hypoalbuminaemia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Hypoalbuminaemia is a laboratory finding characterized by abnormally low levels of albumin in the patient's blood serum. This condition is revealed through patient test results and indicates reduced albumin levels compared to normal ranges. Hypoalbuminaemia serves as an important clinical indicator in medical diagnostics and assessment.&lt;SEP&gt;A laboratory finding indicating low serum albumin levels detected in the patient's blood tests.&lt;SEP&gt;Laboratory finding indicating low serum albumin levels, reflecting hepatic dysfunction.&lt;SEP&gt;Low serum albumin level detected in laboratory results, indicating nutritional deficiency or liver dysfunction.&lt;SEP&gt;A condition revealed by laboratory results characterized by abnormally low levels of albumin in the blood.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e0cf79a93d6937f4e196efd0a76b1c14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed28d4753317331d50864a0ff241202a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-552541f5707dbc91dc2b39f24da42ff3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4fb8802354fa5826fc6a61e1d4703650&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42c5dd7e4b8ae3efca148f8d10f468da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af3da83b586005637f4530b60892346&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-389cb396bf4e6268fa31af66e862032b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93cc887c0186b2515e2821eabf31639d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-735be7666813a3f1eedf039a72df5db3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1693a9d96722a090fabd3e1bd2ba20a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f78e14c615a6efcb86bacdcef718021&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-304f340ad4cf36f85eadeea2200b5890</data>
