    <node id="Adenocarcinoma">
      <data key="d0">Adenocarcinoma</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Adenocarcinoma is a type of malignant tumor that was confirmed through liver biopsy in the patient. This cancer represents the underlying malignant pathology identified in the clinical case. The diagnosis was established through histopathological examination via liver biopsy, a diagnostic procedure that provided definitive confirmation of the malignant nature of the tumor and its specific classification as adenocarcinoma.&lt;SEP&gt;A type of cancer affecting glandular cells, confirmed through liver biopsy.&lt;SEP&gt;A malignant tumor confirmed through liver biopsy, a type of cancer affecting glandular tissues.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e0cf79a93d6937f4e196efd0a76b1c14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-299e0d28d253c37f9dddf4aef8eb2c94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32a4845ff65651415af840aed5ad1767&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12b0793fd5ff30936be7578fadb2f11c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93cc887c0186b2515e2821eabf31639d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-735be7666813a3f1eedf039a72df5db3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17ee3298badd5c634297742f3bfdd8e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd08cbda0f2618e783e7d18b1e718420&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bd68a770018591cf0e4611e9e14ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbdb6e100fb2bdb409feb08c479fa265</data>
