    <node id="Colorectal Cancer">
      <data key="d0">Colorectal Cancer</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Colorectal cancer represents the primary and final diagnosis established for the patient through comprehensive clinical evaluation and diagnostic procedures. This condition is characterized by a malignant tumor originating in the colon or rectum, confirmed through clinical findings, biopsy results, and various diagnostic tests. The diagnosis was substantiated by the patient's clinical presentation, which included rectal bleeding, and the presence of metastatic disease indicating that the cancer has spread beyond the primary tumor site. The malignant nature of this colorectal condition was definitively established based on the integration of clinical evidence, histopathological confirmation via biopsy, and radiological or other diagnostic imaging findings, collectively supporting the diagnosis of colorectal cancer as the patient's definitive diagnosis.&lt;SEP&gt;The primary diagnosis in the patient associated with rectal bleeding and colonic thickening.&lt;SEP&gt;The primary diagnosis for the patient, a cancer of the colon or rectum.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e0cf79a93d6937f4e196efd0a76b1c14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d7dfbf9ae7bdd2da18160509a98a29b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aea77867f87b397c2569ebf2e109e550&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa60f44fc47125398c7ec53a5186865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af3da83b586005637f4530b60892346&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12b0793fd5ff30936be7578fadb2f11c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17ee3298badd5c634297742f3bfdd8e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd08cbda0f2618e783e7d18b1e718420&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b832bffca6f5b953e97047ac37cd38ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbdb6e100fb2bdb409feb08c479fa265</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775168889</data>
