    </node>
    <node id="Neoadjuvant Chemoradiotherapy">
      <data key="d0">Neoadjuvant Chemoradiotherapy</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Neoadjuvant Chemoradiotherapy is a combined treatment approach that integrates chemotherapy and radiotherapy administered prior to surgical intervention. This treatment regimen is initiated as a corrective action for a patient's medical condition, serving as a preparatory therapy before potential surgery. The method combines two therapeutic modalities—chemotherapy (systemic drug treatment) and radiation therapy (targeted energy-based treatment)—delivered concurrently or sequentially before the patient undergoes surgical procedures. By administering this multimodal therapy in the neoadjuvant setting (before surgery), the treatment aims to reduce tumor burden, improve surgical outcomes, and enhance overall patient prognosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Treatment approach involving combined chemotherapy and radiation therapy administered prior to primary treatment, commenced as corrective action.&lt;SEP&gt;Neoadjuvant chemoradiotherapy treatment commenced as corrective action for colorectal cancer management.&lt;SEP&gt;A combination treatment of chemotherapy and radiotherapy administered before surgical intervention for colorectal cancer.&lt;SEP&gt;A treatment approach combining chemotherapy and radiation therapy initiated before definitive surgical intervention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e0cf79a93d6937f4e196efd0a76b1c14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-552541f5707dbc91dc2b39f24da42ff3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93f288f93598c3b3a931faed20b2314c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42c5dd7e4b8ae3efca148f8d10f468da&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32a4845ff65651415af840aed5ad1767&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa60f44fc47125398c7ec53a5186865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-389cb396bf4e6268fa31af66e862032b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93cc887c0186b2515e2821eabf31639d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-735be7666813a3f1eedf039a72df5db3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17ee3298badd5c634297742f3bfdd8e4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b832bffca6f5b953e97047ac37cd38ec&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d99b348010e0859bf79ca469b926378b</data>
