    <node id="IV Antihypertensives">
      <data key="d0">IV Antihypertensives</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">IV Antihypertensives are intravenous medications administered to patients for the management of acute hypertensive conditions and related cardiac emergencies. These medications serve as a primary treatment approach for multiple acute clinical scenarios, including hypertensive urgency, where rapid blood pressure reduction is necessary to prevent organ damage or further complications.

IV Antihypertensives are employed as a corrective action and treatment method for acute cardiac conditions, particularly in cases of acute non-ST elevation myocardial infarction (NSTEMI), where blood pressure control is essential for optimizing myocardial perfusion and reducing cardiac workload. Additionally, these medications are utilized to manage new-onset atrial fibrillation, a condition frequently associated with elevated blood pressure that can precipitate or exacerbate arrhythmias. The administration of IV antihypertensives in this context helps stabilize the patient's hemodynamic status and may facilitate restoration of normal cardiac rhythm.

The therapeutic use of IV Antihypertensives extends to broader management of patients presenting with acute cardiac conditions where systemic blood pressure management is integral to the overall treatment strategy. By providing rapid onset of action inherent to the intravenous route, these medications enable quick response to hypertensive emergencies and urgencies, preventing potential complications such as stroke, myocardial infarction, or end-organ damage. The use of IV Antihypertensives represents a standard intervention in acute care settings for patients requiring immediate blood pressure regulation and hemodynamic stabilization in the context of various acute cardiac presentations.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-590c301f3f3b6ed7e8dd79ff818eb970&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2a418de55ab776ed3382840643ce211c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f98e594c48f4396c9da7f66fe58029d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8b9466306ab7d2011082fa69d4835ba8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af28652606d78849d0249d790f40681f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c2571e07f042a9f93f2e47306fa03981&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-15f9eef500fedf61aecc494b64b11664&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-205b75d592f5c35757c06b25aa8e1984</data>
