    <node id="Stridor">
      <data key="d0">Stridor</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Stridor is an abnormal breathing sound characterized by high-pitched, wheezing noises caused by disrupted airflow through an obstructed airway. It represents an audible breathing abnormality and difficulty that patients report as a presenting symptom during clinical evaluation.

Stridor manifests as an audible indicator of airway obstruction and is classified as an abnormal breathing sound. The condition involves noticeable disruptions to normal respiratory airflow, which patients perceive and report as difficulty breathing or abnormal respiratory sounds during their medical assessment.

In the documented cases, stridor presented with varying durations prior to patient admission. The symptom was reported to have persisted for different lengths of time across presentations, ranging from 5 days to 28 days, with one instance documenting a 7-day duration. These variations reflect the diverse clinical presentations and progression patterns of airway obstruction in affected patients. Regardless of duration, stridor consistently served as a key presenting symptom that prompted medical evaluation and admission.&lt;SEP&gt;An abnormal breathing sound reported as part of the patient's clinical presentation.&lt;SEP&gt;An abnormal breathing sound reported by the patient as part of the clinical presentation.&lt;SEP&gt;A high-pitched breathing sound indicating airway obstruction, present as inspiratory stridor in the patient.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-348a6f93e1df4665db6794f8f475315a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5543cdd6c57fb9e70e4d6b2688e3521&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d5bcc445de13e0cbc298cdc386c5d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c41f1161752e203627b5fc920fca07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-633b98afe9675d274497d13c770dc7a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2fe603f70880276dc53d591b2c6fc6ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa76722cb250ebdc3971241f8d1d7a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ef20424effc0d32c39fcdcec5da83d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeb696350165bf9ae41216f5236c3817&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8ab7539afd48876f5bb300e184ed79b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5211c9d4452573a55519727c0ef76b1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169123</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tuberculosis">
      <data key="d0">Tuberculosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tuberculosis is a prior infectious disease that has been documented in the patient's medical history. This previous tuberculosis infection is relevant to the patient's current clinical presentation and respiratory condition. The documentation of this prior tuberculosis infection appears in the patient's medical records prior to the current admission and serves as an important contextual factor in understanding the patient's present health status and ongoing medical needs.&lt;SEP&gt;Tuberculosis is a prior medical condition in the patient's history.&lt;SEP&gt;A prior infectious disease in the patient's medical history that may have influenced current respiratory condition.&lt;SEP&gt;Prior tuberculosis is part of the patient's relevant medical history.&lt;SEP&gt;Tuberculosis is a relevant prior medical history for the patient.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-348a6f93e1df4665db6794f8f475315a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11944cb5618b1905065e32d7424e5ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74df9a5aaec0ab322e9634e2a357e4ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-680b0868e00cfb2dc1ba062d72742486&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d69e90de14f13f99bd017794598000f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b29acdc1599ff32318f1144aaa062a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b77bea8599e47e5947ec3a7be0ce9b73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ef20424effc0d32c39fcdcec5da83d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dda6359792d27d913bf9dbba5833f91f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ebdec2fe609dbeb73244f6c370f4d8eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a71fb455018aca9558b624f3b05ab137&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51e9f120ecce8be89d00fb7954cbe1a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775168899</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pleural Effusion">
      <data key="d0">Pleural Effusion</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Pleural effusion is an abnormal accumulation of fluid in the pleural space, the area between the lungs and the chest wall. This condition is identified and detected through chest X-ray imaging, which serves as a key diagnostic tool for recognizing the presence of fluid accumulation in this anatomical region. The radiological findings on chest X-ray examination reveal the pathological fluid collection surrounding the lungs, making it a clinically significant observation in pulmonary and thoracic medicine.&lt;SEP&gt;Pleural effusion is a radiological finding indicating abnormal fluid accumulation in the pleural space detected on chest X-ray.&lt;SEP&gt;Pleural effusion is a condition involving abnormal fluid accumulation in the pleural space, identified on chest X-ray.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-348a6f93e1df4665db6794f8f475315a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5543cdd6c57fb9e70e4d6b2688e3521&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92cc2c46c1f49338ed7955ea4238e60f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7f38ad205281fc2b3d3fdc52c5a8b5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c41f1161752e203627b5fc920fca07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74df9a5aaec0ab322e9634e2a357e4ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-680b0868e00cfb2dc1ba062d72742486&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d69e90de14f13f99bd017794598000f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b74bdb93da896529bce41ee41924095c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c4cc1d83b1ff0beb41c0996e0bed59f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775168600</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mediastinal Lymphadenopathy">
      <data key="d0">Mediastinal Lymphadenopathy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Mediastinal lymphadenopathy is a radiological and pathological finding characterized by the enlargement of lymph nodes located in the mediastinum, the central compartment of the thoracic cavity. This condition is primarily detected and identified through computed tomography (CT) imaging of the thorax, which serves as the standard diagnostic imaging modality for visualizing and confirming enlarged mediastinal lymph nodes. Mediastinal lymphadenopathy represents an abnormal condition in which lymph nodes in this anatomical region become enlarged beyond normal size, and this enlargement can be observed as a distinct imaging finding on CT thorax scans. The presence of mediastinal lymphadenopathy on imaging is significant as it may indicate underlying pathological processes requiring further clinical evaluation and investigation to determine the underlying etiology.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-348a6f93e1df4665db6794f8f475315a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7f38ad205281fc2b3d3fdc52c5a8b5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b77bea8599e47e5947ec3a7be0ce9b73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b74bdb93da896529bce41ee41924095c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8ef20424effc0d32c39fcdcec5da83d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a71fb455018aca9558b624f3b05ab137&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51e9f120ecce8be89d00fb7954cbe1a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c7f5f1efa9fe1ad162b412383e280bf</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169029</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pulmonary Fibrosis">
      <data key="d0">Pulmonary Fibrosis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Pulmonary Fibrosis is a chronic lung disease characterized by progressive scarring and stiffening of lung tissue. The condition involves the formation of scar tissue within the lungs, which leads to tissue consolidation and reduced lung elasticity. This progressive nature of the disease means that the scarring and stiffening of lung tissue worsens over time, resulting in increasingly compromised lung function. Pulmonary Fibrosis has been established as the primary diagnosis for the patient based on clinical presentation and imaging findings. The disease manifests through the gradual replacement of normal lung tissue with fibrous scar tissue, which impairs the lungs' ability to function properly and causes the characteristic stiffness associated with the condition.&lt;SEP&gt;Pulmonary fibrosis is the established diagnosis for the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;Pulmonary fibrosis is the established diagnosis for the patient based on clinical findings and diagnostic results.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-348a6f93e1df4665db6794f8f475315a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5543cdd6c57fb9e70e4d6b2688e3521&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf05a1180370ca5c22ffbfcdb89ab2d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d69e90de14f13f99bd017794598000f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50c06f071bd4436025fb35de50515fda&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b77bea8599e47e5947ec3a7be0ce9b73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeb696350165bf9ae41216f5236c3817&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8ab7539afd48876f5bb300e184ed79b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a71fb455018aca9558b624f3b05ab137&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51e9f120ecce8be89d00fb7954cbe1a</data>
