      <data key="d0">Decompensated Heart Failure</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">A cardiac condition characterized by impaired heart function, diagnosed in the patient through clinical examination and diagnostic testing.&lt;SEP&gt;Decompensated heart failure is the primary diagnosis given to the patient, characterized by cardiac dysfunction.&lt;SEP&gt;A cardiac condition diagnosed in the patient characterized by reduced ejection fraction of 35% and irregular heart rhythm.&lt;SEP&gt;A cardiac condition diagnosed in the patient characterized by impaired heart function, elevated jugular venous pressure, and regional wall motion abnormality.&lt;SEP&gt;The primary diagnosis given to the patient, indicating acute worsening of heart failure.&lt;SEP&gt;A cardiac condition diagnosed in the patient, characterized by the inability of the heart to pump blood effectively.&lt;SEP&gt;The primary diagnosis indicating acute deterioration of the patient's cardiac function.</data>
