    <node id="Mixed Pattern">
      <data key="d0">Mixed Pattern</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Mixed Pattern refers to a pulmonary function test result that demonstrates both obstructive and restrictive components of lung disease simultaneously. This finding indicates combined obstructive and restrictive respiratory dysfunction in a patient, reflecting a pattern of pulmonary dysfunction that encompasses characteristics of both disease types.

In a Mixed Pattern result, the pulmonary function test identifies the coexistence of obstructive and restrictive respiratory impairment, rather than showing evidence of only one type of pathology. This dual presentation suggests that the patient's lungs are affected by conditions or processes that both limit airflow (obstructive component) and reduce overall lung capacity or compliance (restrictive component). The identification of a Mixed Pattern on pulmonary function testing is clinically significant as it indicates more complex underlying pulmonary pathology that may require comprehensive diagnostic evaluation and targeted therapeutic intervention addressing both obstructive and restrictive aspects of the patient's respiratory dysfunction.&lt;SEP&gt;A pulmonary function test result indicating both obstructive and restrictive components.&lt;SEP&gt;A lung function finding indicated by pulmonary function tests, representing a combination of obstructive and restrictive patterns.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-3758214300d6bd794534d0e32e9bd057&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92cc2c46c1f49338ed7955ea4238e60f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7f38ad205281fc2b3d3fdc52c5a8b5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b29acdc1599ff32318f1144aaa062a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-50c06f071bd4436025fb35de50515fda&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b77bea8599e47e5947ec3a7be0ce9b73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa76722cb250ebdc3971241f8d1d7a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeb696350165bf9ae41216f5236c3817&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8ab7539afd48876f5bb300e184ed79b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4f335b1b7bae18006bc038ab4128db1</data>
