    <node id="Productive Cough">
      <data key="d0">Productive Cough</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Productive Cough

Productive cough is a respiratory symptom characterized by coughing that produces mucus or sputum secretion. This symptom is reported by patients as a primary manifestation of their underlying condition. The presentations of productive cough documented in clinical records vary considerably in duration and context.

The documented durations of productive cough range from acute to chronic presentations. The shortest documented duration is 3 weeks, while some patients present with more prolonged manifestations lasting up to 28 weeks. Intermediate presentations include a 5-week history noted upon patient admission, a 10-week duration documented in multiple records, a 14-week persistent symptom, and a 21-week presentation. The most extended documented case spans 28 weeks, with the symptom characterized by consistent cough with mucus or sputum production throughout this period.

Productive cough represents a clinically significant symptom that warrants medical evaluation, as the wide range of documented durations—from several weeks to multiple months—suggests varying underlying etiologies or disease severity. The consistency of sputum production across all documented cases indicates an active pathological process affecting the respiratory tract, distinguishing this symptom from a dry cough and suggesting potential infection, inflammation, or other pulmonary conditions requiring further diagnostic investigation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-92cc2c46c1f49338ed7955ea4238e60f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c35da8135a5d590d4accdb1b51d149c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11944cb5618b1905065e32d7424e5ea1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-27c41f1161752e203627b5fc920fca07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8e4a466aae7fe4bee947643e66e2ba9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeb696350165bf9ae41216f5236c3817&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8ab7539afd48876f5bb300e184ed79b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c7f5f1efa9fe1ad162b412383e280bf</data>
