    <node id="Syncope">
      <data key="d0">Syncope</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Syncope is a medical symptom characterized by a temporary loss of consciousness or fainting experienced by the patient. This symptom formed a significant part of the patient's presenting complaints and chief complaint during clinical evaluation. The episodes of syncope occurred over a period of approximately 21 days, indicating a recurring pattern of loss of consciousness events. Syncope manifests as transient episodes where the patient experiences fainting or complete loss of awareness, contributing to the overall clinical presentation that prompted medical assessment and intervention.&lt;SEP&gt;A symptom of fainting or loss of consciousness presented by the patient.</data>
