    <node id="Rheumatoid Arthritis">
      <data key="d0">Rheumatoid Arthritis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">An autoimmune disease characterized by inflammation of joints, diagnosed in the patient based on clinical findings and diagnostic tests.&lt;SEP&gt;An autoimmune disease diagnosed in the patient based on positive RF and anti-CCP antibodies and clinical presentation.&lt;SEP&gt;The diagnosed condition affecting the patient, characterized by joint inflammation and related symptoms.&lt;SEP&gt;Rheumatoid arthritis is an autoimmune inflammatory condition characterized by joint inflammation, affecting the shoulder and sacroiliac joints in this patient.&lt;SEP&gt;An autoimmune inflammatory disease diagnosed in the patient, characterized by periarticular erosions, sacroiliitis, and negatively birefringent crystals in synovial fluid.&lt;SEP&gt;The diagnosed condition characterized by progressive stiffness affecting the spine, elevated uric acid levels, and chondrocalcinosis findings.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-91f2e17beb9f3d24b9faa9059ed6acae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e6cfcb84271ca620400ff56bfc7cd22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57d53deb985a155d9d6cc2e16d224de8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5688d8714c141858552becb5c4be710&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d745ec6e17e6c423c81b61841434f2ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c717ae7fe86b3a6ae2271e48ba22e47</data>
