    <node id="Elevated Uric Acid">
      <data key="d0">Elevated Uric Acid</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Elevated Uric Acid is a laboratory finding identified through blood tests that reveals abnormally high concentrations of uric acid in a patient's blood. This condition represents a biochemical abnormality detected via standard blood test results. The elevated levels of uric acid indicate that the patient's serum uric acid concentration exceeds normal reference ranges, which can have clinical significance for various metabolic and rheumatologic conditions. The detection of elevated uric acid through blood testing serves as an important diagnostic marker in clinical practice.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood test result showing elevated uric acid levels in the patient.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-91f2e17beb9f3d24b9faa9059ed6acae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05e39d703a228f9f75806162f2ec5ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47645b674af4f2a88a64e49657a83073&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c89e4f390f742775decbbc049992e1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a10d7b819d49867b6e7814e98a516ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68e7577c18cbc865ebf744daec101377&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57d53deb985a155d9d6cc2e16d224de8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2125b75a0cbbb2f0ed02f43f4bdbc9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c717ae7fe86b3a6ae2271e48ba22e47</data>
