    <node id="Sacroiliitis">
      <data key="d0">Sacroiliitis</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Sacroiliitis is an inflammatory condition affecting the sacroiliac joint or joints. The condition is characterized by inflammation localized to this anatomical structure and is typically identified and demonstrated through magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) examination. MRI imaging serves as the primary diagnostic tool for detecting and confirming the presence of sacroiliitis in affected patients, allowing for clear visualization of the inflammatory changes within the sacroiliac joint tissue.&lt;SEP&gt;Sacroiliitis is inflammation of the sacroiliac joint detected on MRI imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;Inflammation of the sacroiliac joint detected on MRI, associated with rheumatoid arthritis.&lt;SEP&gt;Inflammation of the sacroiliac joints demonstrated by MRI findings in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;An inflammatory condition of the sacroiliac joint demonstrated on MRI imaging.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-91f2e17beb9f3d24b9faa9059ed6acae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5ef4a9ff207d5fcf312fa4948419500&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5da01a385b47958d437c2b60db9a3505&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1de22df34c77d7bc601fa40ded28a01&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a667de4da28bb439da82a6fd3153ca1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3303df334fce5c6456df7e61e6203291&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-996a573759ff4451282c4bad9069e599&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86ab66027f34b355354509e6cc65735e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d5688d8714c141858552becb5c4be710&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d745ec6e17e6c423c81b61841434f2ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2125b75a0cbbb2f0ed02f43f4bdbc9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f0cb44df10264318173904dd8b4a1b9e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775168876</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Total Knee Replacement">
      <data key="d0">Total Knee Replacement</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Total Knee Replacement is a surgical intervention performed to manage and treat various musculoskeletal conditions affecting the knee joint. This surgical management procedure addresses joint damage and dysfunction, restoring function and alleviating symptoms in patients with compromised knee integrity.

Total Knee Replacement serves as a treatment option for multiple clinical conditions. It is commonly performed to address rheumatoid arthritis and associated knee instability, providing surgical management for patients whose conditions have not responded adequately to conservative treatments. Additionally, Total Knee Replacement may be utilized in the surgical management of systemic lupus erythematosus when the disease process has resulted in significant knee joint pathology.

The procedure involves surgical intervention designed to restore proper knee function and reduce pain in patients experiencing degenerative or inflammatory musculoskeletal conditions. By addressing the underlying joint damage and dysfunction, Total Knee Replacement aims to improve patient mobility and quality of life.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-91f2e17beb9f3d24b9faa9059ed6acae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0ff99b3fbcf99c238b4ecf7d0e0a7afc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c89e4f390f742775decbbc049992e1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e6cfcb84271ca620400ff56bfc7cd22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68e7577c18cbc865ebf744daec101377&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c623dc26c99ebd3a6caf0a7b69babb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57d53deb985a155d9d6cc2e16d224de8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c717ae7fe86b3a6ae2271e48ba22e47</data>
