    <node id="Blood Cultures">
      <data key="d0">Blood Cultures</data>
      <data key="d1">artifact</data>
      <data key="d2">Blood Cultures

Blood cultures are laboratory tests performed to detect bacterial or fungal infections in the bloodstream through microbial culture analysis of blood samples. This diagnostic procedure involves culturing blood samples to identify potential pathogens that may indicate systemic infection.

The results of blood cultures can vary significantly depending on the patient and clinical context. In some cases, blood cultures have returned negative results, ruling out the presence of bacterial infection in the bloodstream and indicating an absence of detectable pathogens. In other instances, blood cultures have yielded positive results, identifying specific bacterial organisms. Notable positive findings have included the growth of Streptococcus pneumoniae and Staphylococcus aureus, both of which indicate bacterial infection requiring clinical intervention.

Blood cultures are commonly performed as part of a diagnostic workup when bacterial or fungal infection is suspected. In clinical practice, blood cultures may be pending at the time of initial treatment, with results becoming available after the testing process is complete. The results of these cultures are critical for confirming or excluding bloodstream infection and for guiding appropriate antimicrobial therapy based on the identified organism and its susceptibilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Laboratory test performed on the patient that returned negative results.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood cultures are a diagnostic method used to identify bacterial pathogens in the patient's blood.&lt;SEP&gt;Laboratory test that was pending at the time of treatment initiation.&lt;SEP&gt;Laboratory test that identified Streptococcus pneumoniae in the patient's blood.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6d5bcc445de13e0cbc298cdc386c5d44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-633b98afe9675d274497d13c770dc7a8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-664a546642468c69e4060dadf0cf6259&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d8c12fa6d02482beb80341b410dc4fc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edefebc0c0ccf297dd9120097036b554&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cd85436604dc21edf42918a59c026df6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c464148080eca020535a45a857530061&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8eff0da2c4db4508c02bd09795c327d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e94bd709d2e35b86324f9ebf8cb380f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea49e51c9a44c10ef5253c942a3bd509&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb2cd72190b2ba60ab4d0ac08898df5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5211c9d4452573a55519727c0ef76b1</data>
