    <node id="Rigid Bronchoscopy">
      <data key="d0">Rigid Bronchoscopy</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">An urgent surgical procedure performed under general anaesthesia to visualize and remove foreign bodies from the respiratory tract.&lt;SEP&gt;An urgent invasive procedure involving inspection of the bronchial airways using a rigid instrument.&lt;SEP&gt;Rigid bronchoscopy under general anaesthesia is the urgent corrective procedure initiated to address the suspected foreign body aspiration.&lt;SEP&gt;An urgent surgical procedure performed under general anaesthesia to address the airway obstruction.</data>
