    <node id="Acute Territorial Infarct">
      <data key="d0">Acute Territorial Infarct</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">An area of tissue death in the brain territory supplied by the middle cerebral artery, identified on imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;A finding on MRI brain showing acute stroke in the middle cerebral artery distribution.&lt;SEP&gt;An acute territorial infarct in MCA distribution is a brain stroke affecting the middle cerebral artery territory, identified on MRI.&lt;SEP&gt;Brain tissue necrosis in the middle cerebral artery distribution observed on MRI imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;A region of tissue death in the middle cerebral artery distribution area caused by restricted blood supply.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-ce7467c36645566972e9f92c5fea2ee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a34ac93aa94bca40ac3bced0aa9de86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4fd7d8854cca43bc54c0fae9bacd07a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d21fe1428431fa9900c5bdf9740d3490&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-035214426d6755454aa9eb73b6e0d4e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c15b0cde6ec5d9e10908aa2ac3619ac</data>
