      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">The anatomical distribution of the middle cerebral artery in the brain, indicating the location of the infarct.&lt;SEP&gt;The area of the brain supplied by the middle cerebral artery where the infarct occurred.&lt;SEP&gt;MCA distribution refers to the anatomical territory supplied by the middle cerebral artery.&lt;SEP&gt;The anatomical area supplied by the middle cerebral artery where the acute infarct occurred.&lt;SEP&gt;The territory supplied by the middle cerebral artery in the brain.&lt;SEP&gt;The middle cerebral artery distribution where the acute territorial infarct was located in the patient's brain.</data>
