    <node id="Diffuse Leptomeningeal Enhancement">
      <data key="d0">Diffuse Leptomeningeal Enhancement</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Diffuse Leptomeningeal Enhancement is an MRI imaging finding characterized by widespread enhancement of the leptomeninges, the delicate innermost meningeal layers that surround the brain and spinal cord. This radiological finding appears on MRI brain imaging as an area of increased signal intensity affecting the meningeal structures throughout the brain.

Diffuse Leptomeningeal Enhancement indicates inflammation or infection of the meningeal layers. The presence of this enhancement pattern on MRI suggests involvement of the leptomeninges, which can result from various pathological processes affecting these sensitive tissues surrounding the central nervous system. The diffuse nature of the enhancement indicates that the inflammatory or infectious process is widespread rather than localized to a specific region, reflecting systemic or extensive involvement of the meningeal structures.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-163a075cd3f1260ecb6825df91ee03e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3052227d42277d8826362c90a01ca5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4881dc7c4d5f1079552b2430a7677765&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba602c293552d3d1cc227f2fb935fe2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6d9ce3f21c7d4f0447f68d282ddba6e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd187f61bb50ddf67fed66dbf47414b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66d79432cfb5da18b1aac0a6d772e676&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3cde4a56707d1854488f0b25ff33596</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775168975</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Xanthochromia">
      <data key="d0">Xanthochromia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Xanthochromia is a clinical finding characterized by yellowish discoloration of cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) detected during CSF analysis. This discoloration serves as an important diagnostic indicator of various underlying pathological processes.

Xanthochromia typically indicates previous or ongoing hemorrhage within the central nervous system, as the yellow coloration results from blood breakdown products present in the CSF. The presence of these breakdown products suggests that bleeding has occurred in the subarachnoid space or other CNS compartments. Beyond hemorrhage, xanthochromia can also be associated with meningeal involvement and inflammation, as well as elevated protein levels in the cerebrospinal fluid. Additionally, the finding may indicate prior or concurrent infection affecting the meninges.

The detection of xanthochromia during cerebrospinal fluid analysis is significant for clinical diagnosis and evaluation of CNS pathology. It represents a visible manifestation of pathological processes affecting the brain and spinal cord, helping clinicians identify conditions such as subarachnoid hemorrhage, meningitis, and other serious neurological disorders. The presence of this finding in CSF samples warrants further investigation to determine the underlying cause and guide appropriate clinical management.&lt;SEP&gt;CSF finding characterized by yellow discoloration indicating blood breakdown products.&lt;SEP&gt;Yellow discoloration of cerebrospinal fluid observed in CSF analysis of the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A finding demonstrated in cerebrospinal fluid analysis indicating blood breakdown products in the CSF.&lt;SEP&gt;A cerebrospinal fluid finding indicating the presence of discoloration, suggesting possible subarachnoid hemorrhage or infection.&lt;SEP&gt;Xanthochromia is a yellowish discoloration of cerebrospinal fluid indicating previous bleeding or blood breakdown products.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-163a075cd3f1260ecb6825df91ee03e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3052227d42277d8826362c90a01ca5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1911d102d00d5197ec74e282f36fbad9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4881dc7c4d5f1079552b2430a7677765&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbc516b53c71727bd08346a19ee50251&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c15b0cde6ec5d9e10908aa2ac3619ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f26c6d54ddb9d4b1f92d2f09061da7f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66d79432cfb5da18b1aac0a6d772e676&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3cde4a56707d1854488f0b25ff33596&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d94401800c111b74bf53e07ee0975662&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b934702b442931687944c3b680751df6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2747605a19dd90cae3b9e6a20d1194f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1405b111c59c1691a48901cde2eed51b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169185</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Burst Suppression Pattern">
      <data key="d0">Burst Suppression Pattern</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Burst Suppression Pattern is an abnormal electroencephalogram (EEG) finding characterized by alternating periods of electrical activity and suppression. This distinctive EEG pattern manifests as cycles of bursts of brain electrical activity interspersed with periods of relative silence or suppression, creating an alternating pattern that is readily observable in patient recordings. The pattern reflects severe neurological dysfunction and represents a significant deviation from normal brain electrical activity. The defining feature of Burst Suppression Pattern is the regular cyclical alternation between periods when measurable electrical activity is present in the brain and periods when electrical activity is markedly reduced or absent, resulting in the characteristic appearance of bursts followed by intervals of suppression on the electroencephalogram.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-163a075cd3f1260ecb6825df91ee03e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4881dc7c4d5f1079552b2430a7677765&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba602c293552d3d1cc227f2fb935fe2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6bd187f61bb50ddf67fed66dbf47414b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c15b0cde6ec5d9e10908aa2ac3619ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f26c6d54ddb9d4b1f92d2f09061da7f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d94401800c111b74bf53e07ee0975662&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3b72ae1dccac058d727442c28727b3d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169193</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ischaemic Stroke">
      <data key="d0">Ischaemic Stroke</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Ischaemic Stroke is a cerebrovascular condition characterized by interrupted or reduced blood flow to the brain, resulting in acute neurological deficits. The condition was diagnosed in the patient based on clinical presentation and imaging findings that confirmed acute territorial infarction in the middle cerebral artery distribution.

The patient presented with sudden onset of severe neurological symptoms. These symptoms included severe headache, visual disturbance, motor deficits, left-sided hemiplegia, ataxia, and dysphasia. The constellation of these clinical manifestations reflected the acute ischemic event affecting brain tissue supplied by the middle cerebral artery. The sudden onset of these neurological symptoms, combined with imaging evidence of infarction, established ischaemic stroke as the primary diagnosis. The reduced blood flow to affected brain regions resulted in the loss of neurological function corresponding to the territory of the compromised cerebral vasculature.&lt;SEP&gt;A diagnosis of ischaemic stroke characterized by altered consciousness, hemiplegia, and dysphasia in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;The primary diagnosis for the patient, characterized by reduced blood flow to brain tissue.&lt;SEP&gt;Final diagnosis of the patient characterized by restricted blood supply to the brain.&lt;SEP&gt;A neurological condition diagnosed in the patient, characterized by sudden onset of speech disturbance, neck stiffness, right facial droop, and hyperreflexia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-163a075cd3f1260ecb6825df91ee03e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3052227d42277d8826362c90a01ca5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a34ac93aa94bca40ac3bced0aa9de86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4881dc7c4d5f1079552b2430a7677765&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-035214426d6755454aa9eb73b6e0d4e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbc516b53c71727bd08346a19ee50251&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-df174d639a33c9effb2f0ce6df80ce71&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c15b0cde6ec5d9e10908aa2ac3619ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f26c6d54ddb9d4b1f92d2f09061da7f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-66d79432cfb5da18b1aac0a6d772e676&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3cde4a56707d1854488f0b25ff33596&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b934702b442931687944c3b680751df6</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169080</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
