    <node id="Pruritus">
      <data key="d0">Pruritus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Pruritus is a symptom characterized by an itching sensation that manifests in patients across various clinical presentations. This symptom is commonly associated with gastrointestinal conditions, where patients experience persistent or severe itching as part of their overall clinical picture. Pruritus may present alongside other gastrointestinal manifestations, notably rectal bleeding, where the itching sensation occurs concurrent with hemorrhagic symptoms.

In some clinical contexts, pruritus is specifically linked to hepatobiliary conditions, where the itching represents an important associated symptom of the underlying pathology. The severity of pruritus can vary, ranging from mild to severe itching sensations that impact the patient's clinical presentation. This symptom is recognized as a significant component of patient symptomatology and is documented as an associated finding that warrants clinical attention and consideration in the diagnostic and therapeutic approach to managing the patient's underlying condition.&lt;SEP&gt;Itching symptom associated with the patient's clinical presentation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-299e0d28d253c37f9dddf4aef8eb2c94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93f288f93598c3b3a931faed20b2314c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6540caa7beb945f0321bf38942587d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa60f44fc47125398c7ec53a5186865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12b0793fd5ff30936be7578fadb2f11c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9bd68a770018591cf0e4611e9e14ae0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d99b348010e0859bf79ca469b926378b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f78e14c615a6efcb86bacdcef718021&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1375b9b5b2e11625f9232d34b4107e38</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169151</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pale Stools">
      <data key="d0">Pale Stools</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Abnormal stool coloration indicating potential biliary or liver dysfunction in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;Pale stools are a clinical symptom associated with the patient's gastrointestinal presentation.&lt;SEP&gt;A clinical sign observed in the patient indicating abnormal stool coloration.&lt;SEP&gt;A symptom characterized by abnormal stool appearance experienced by the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A clinical symptom indicating blood loss in the gastrointestinal tract, presented by the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A symptom characterized by lighter-colored stool, indicating potential gastrointestinal bleeding.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-299e0d28d253c37f9dddf4aef8eb2c94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-32a4845ff65651415af840aed5ad1767&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-caa60f44fc47125398c7ec53a5186865&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2af3da83b586005637f4530b60892346&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bd08cbda0f2618e783e7d18b1e718420&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbdb6e100fb2bdb409feb08c479fa265</data>
