      <data key="d0">Critical Severity</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Critical Severity indicates the high-risk status of the patient's clinical condition requiring emergency intervention.&lt;SEP&gt;The severity level assigned to the clinical case indicating a critical and life-threatening condition.&lt;SEP&gt;Critical severity indicates the serious nature of the patient's clinical condition.&lt;SEP&gt;Critical severity level assigned to the clinical case indicating the serious nature of the patient's condition.&lt;SEP&gt;Critical severity indicates the urgent and life-threatening nature of the patient's clinical condition.&lt;SEP&gt;Critical severity is the severity level assigned to this clinical case, indicating the urgency and seriousness of the patient's condition.</data>
