    <node id="Cranial Nerve Palsy">
      <data key="d0">Cranial Nerve Palsy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Cranial Nerve Palsy is a neurological condition characterized by dysfunction or paralysis of one or more cranial nerves. This condition manifests as an impairment of cranial nerve function and is identified during neurological examination of the patient. The diagnosis and assessment of cranial nerve palsy depend on clinical evaluation through systematic neurological examination, which reveals the specific cranial nerve involvement and the extent of functional compromise affecting the patient.</data>
