    </node>
    <node id="Status Epilepticus">
      <data key="d0">Status Epilepticus</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Status epilepticus is a neurological condition characterized by prolonged or recurring seizures, diagnosed in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A serious neurological condition involving prolonged seizures, diagnosed in the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A neurological condition characterized by continuous seizures or prolonged seizure activity, diagnosed in the patient through EEG showing burst suppression pattern.&lt;SEP&gt;A neurological emergency condition characterized by prolonged seizures, diagnosed in the patient and treated with medication.&lt;SEP&gt;Status epilepticus is the primary diagnosis given to the patient, a serious neurological condition.&lt;SEP&gt;The primary diagnosis of the patient, characterized by prolonged or recurrent seizures.&lt;SEP&gt;Status epilepticus is a neurological emergency characterized by prolonged or repeated seizures without full consciousness recovery between episodes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d4fd7d8854cca43bc54c0fae9bacd07a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d21fe1428431fa9900c5bdf9740d3490&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba602c293552d3d1cc227f2fb935fe2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a0808ea5951fe6ba96ffa3ee735cda17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-84e342b229c6a006856ecdc1a267768a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2747605a19dd90cae3b9e6a20d1194f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1405b111c59c1691a48901cde2eed51b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169186</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Moderate Functional Recovery">
      <data key="d0">Moderate Functional Recovery</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Moderate Functional Recovery

Moderate functional recovery is a clinical outcome observed in patients at discharge following medical or surgical treatment. This outcome is characterized by partial restoration of normal function and substantial but not complete restoration of functional capacity. Rather than achieving full pre-illness functionality, patients experiencing moderate functional recovery demonstrate meaningful improvement from their baseline condition at the time of treatment initiation, though some functional limitations may persist.

Moderate functional recovery can occur across various clinical contexts and treatment modalities. In neurological conditions, this outcome has been documented following treatments such as IV alteplase thrombolysis combined with antiplatelet therapy, where patients exhibit moderate improvement in neurological function at discharge. Moderate functional recovery has also been observed as a discharge outcome in patients treated for other conditions, including primary CNS lymphoma, where treatment interventions result in partial restoration of patient function rather than complete resolution of symptoms or deficits.

The achievement of moderate functional recovery at discharge represents a clinically meaningful improvement, indicating that the applied therapeutic interventions have produced substantial benefits to patient functionality, even though complete restoration to pre-morbid levels may not have been attained. This outcome classification reflects the clinical reality that many patients experience meaningful recovery trajectories without achieving full functional restoration, positioning moderate functional recovery as an important intermediate outcome between minimal functional recovery and complete functional recovery in clinical assessment frameworks.&lt;SEP&gt;The patient's clinical outcome at discharge showing improvement in neurological function following treatment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d4fd7d8854cca43bc54c0fae9bacd07a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d21fe1428431fa9900c5bdf9740d3490&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-903baf97d86d9b7dd49873c2407977ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c15b0cde6ec5d9e10908aa2ac3619ac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f26c6d54ddb9d4b1f92d2f09061da7f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d94401800c111b74bf53e07ee0975662&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2747605a19dd90cae3b9e6a20d1194f3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1405b111c59c1691a48901cde2eed51b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3b72ae1dccac058d727442c28727b3d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1775169193</data>
