      <data key="d0">Squamous Cell Carcinoma In Situ</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Squamous cell carcinoma in situ is a type of skin malignancy identified in the patient's biopsy results.&lt;SEP&gt;A histopathological finding from skin biopsy indicating early-stage malignant transformation of squamous cells.&lt;SEP&gt;A type of skin cancer identified through biopsy of the patient's lesion.&lt;SEP&gt;A precancerous skin lesion diagnosis, abbreviated as SCC in situ, representing the clinical diagnosis for the patient.&lt;SEP&gt;A type of skin cancer confined to the epidermis, also known as Bowen's disease, identified through skin biopsy.</data>
