    <edge source="Meniscal Tear" target="MRI">
      <data key="d7">8.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The relation between MRI and meniscal tear refers to the diagnostic capability of Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) to detect and demonstrate the presence of meniscal tears in patients. MRI imaging serves as an effective diagnostic tool for identifying meniscal tears, which are structural injuries affecting the meniscus of the knee. Through MRI imaging, clinicians can visualize and confirm the presence of meniscal tears, enabling accurate diagnosis of this knee pathology. The relation highlights the clinical utility of MRI as a diagnostic modality for detecting meniscal injuries in affected patients.</data>
      <data key="d9">diagnostic evidence,diagnostic finding,diagnostic result,imaging finding,imaging findings,imaging method,imaging result,pathology detection,structural abnormality,structural damage</data>
