    <edge source="MRI" target="Sacroiliitis">
      <data key="d7">9.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The relation between MRI and Sacroiliitis describes the diagnostic capability of Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) in detecting and demonstrating sacroiliitis, which is an inflammatory condition affecting the sacroiliac joint. Through MRI examination, sacroiliitis can be identified as a diagnostic finding in patients. MRI imaging serves as an effective diagnostic tool for visualizing the inflammation of the sacroiliac joint and confirming the presence of sacroiliitis in clinical assessments.&lt;SEP&gt;MRI demonstrated sacroiliitis in the patient.</data>
