    <edge source="MRI" target="Synovitis">
      <data key="d7">8.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The relation between MRI and Synovitis describes the diagnostic capability of Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) to detect and visualize synovitis in affected joints. MRI imaging is effective in demonstrating synovitis, which represents inflammation of the synovial membrane lining the joints.

MRI has been shown to identify synovitis across multiple anatomical locations. Specifically, MRI imaging can detect synovitis in the knee joint, as well as in the shoulder joint. More broadly, MRI demonstrates synovitis in affected joints and affected areas throughout the body, providing evidence of joint inflammation in patients.

This imaging modality serves as an important diagnostic tool for identifying and assessing the presence and extent of synovitis in patients with joint pathology, enabling clinicians to visualize inflammatory changes within affected joints and guide clinical decision-making regarding diagnosis and treatment.</data>
      <data key="d9">diagnostic evidence,diagnostic observation,diagnostic result,imaging finding,imaging modality,imaging result,joint inflammation,pathological finding,radiological finding</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-6f3968a1e0f64443d559f9c75594cad0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05e39d703a228f9f75806162f2ec5ed2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-47645b674af4f2a88a64e49657a83073&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-858effb6f3bd62fa4b2171b7a13e1257&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1367d2b19d4c80169f6e3f681823cd2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a10d7b819d49867b6e7814e98a516ca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c623dc26c99ebd3a6caf0a7b69babb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57d53deb985a155d9d6cc2e16d224de8</data>
