    <edge source="CSF Analysis" target="Xanthochromia">
      <data key="d7">9.0</data>
      <data key="d8">CSF Analysis and Xanthochromia

CSF analysis demonstrated xanthochromia as a significant laboratory finding in the patient's cerebrospinal fluid. Xanthochromia, detected through CSF analysis, indicates the presence of previous hemorrhage or elevated protein levels within the cerebrospinal fluid. This finding represents an important diagnostic marker in clinical assessment, as the yellow or amber discoloration of the CSF observed during analysis typically reflects the breakdown products of hemoglobin from prior bleeding events or the accumulation of proteins in the central nervous system. The detection of xanthochromia through cerebrospinal fluid examination serves as a crucial laboratory indicator for identifying conditions associated with intracranial hemorrhage or other pathological processes affecting the brain and spinal cord.&lt;SEP&gt;CSF analysis demonstrated the presence of xanthochromia in the cerebrospinal fluid sample.</data>
      <data key="d9">CSF characteristic,diagnostic finding,diagnostic result,fluid analysis result,laboratory finding,laboratory result</data>
