    <edge source="CT Abdomen" target="Intrahepatic Biliary Dilatation">
      <data key="d7">8.0</data>
      <data key="d8">CT Abdomen with Intrahepatic Biliary Dilatation

The relation between CT abdomen imaging and intrahepatic biliary dilatation refers to the radiological findings observed during computed tomography examination of the abdominal region. CT abdomen imaging revealed the presence of intrahepatic biliary dilatation as a significant radiological finding in affected patients. This imaging modality consistently demonstrated dilation of the intrahepatic bile ducts, representing an important diagnostic observation on abdominal computed tomography scans. The detection of intrahepatic biliary dilatation on CT abdomen imaging serves as a key radiological indicator that may warrant further clinical investigation and management considerations.</data>
