    <edge source="Liver Biopsy" target="Hepatocellular Carcinoma">
      <data key="d7">9.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The relation between Hepatocellular Carcinoma and Liver Biopsy is characterized by the use of liver biopsy as a diagnostic confirmation method for hepatocellular carcinoma. Liver biopsy examination serves as a confirmatory procedure that establishes the definitive diagnosis of hepatocellular carcinoma in patients. Through this histopathological examination, the presence of hepatocellular carcinoma can be confirmed, providing pathological evidence essential for clinical diagnosis and subsequent treatment planning. The liver biopsy procedure functions as a critical diagnostic tool that validates the presence of this primary liver malignancy, thereby confirming the condition in affected patients and enabling appropriate clinical management decisions.&lt;SEP&gt;Liver biopsy confirmed hepatocellular carcinoma.</data>
