    <edge source="CT Thorax" target="Cavitating Lesion">
      <data key="d7">10.0</data>
      <data key="d8">CT Thorax, Cavitating Lesion

CT thorax imaging revealed a cavitating lesion as a significant diagnostic finding in the patient. The cavitating lesion was identified within the patient's lungs and thoracic region through CT thorax examination. This finding represents an important clinical observation on imaging studies, indicating the presence of a cavity-forming lesion in the pulmonary tissue. The consistent detection of this lesion across multiple imaging assessments underscores its presence as a notable feature requiring clinical attention and further diagnostic evaluation.&lt;SEP&gt;CT thorax revealed a cavitating lesion as a significant radiological finding.&lt;SEP&gt;CT thorax revealed a cavitating lesion in the patient.</data>
