    <edge source="CT Thorax" target="Honeycombing Pattern">
      <data key="d7">11.0</data>
      <data key="d8">CT Thorax with Honeycombing Pattern represents a radiological finding observed on computed tomography imaging of the chest. The honeycombing pattern is a characteristic radiological appearance that indicates advanced lung disease, specifically pulmonary fibrosis. This pattern is identified within the patient's lungs and lung tissue during CT thorax examination.

The honeycombing pattern on CT thorax serves as a diagnostic indicator of advanced lung fibrosis, reflecting significant structural changes in pulmonary tissue. This finding is consistently recognized as a hallmark radiological feature associated with progressive and advanced stages of lung fibrosis, demonstrating the severity of underlying lung pathology detected through thoracic imaging.&lt;SEP&gt;The CT thorax revealed a honey&lt;SEP&gt;CT thorax revealed honeycombing pattern indicative of pulmonary fibrosis.&lt;SEP&gt;The CT thorax examination revealed a honeycombing pattern indicating chronic lung changes.</data>
