    <edge source="Bronchoscopy" target="Purulent Secretions">
      <data key="d7">12.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The relation between Bronchoscopy and Purulent Secretions describes a clinical finding observed during the bronchoscopic examination of a patient's respiratory tract. Bronchoscopy, an endoscopic procedure that allows direct visualization of the airways, revealed the presence of purulent secretions within the patient's airways. Purulent secretions are thick, yellowish or greenish fluid discharge characteristic of bacterial infection and inflammation of the respiratory tract.

The observation of purulent secretions during bronchoscopy serves as an important clinical indicator, as their presence suggests an underlying bacterial infection within the patient's airways. This finding is significant in clinical assessment and diagnosis, as it helps clinicians identify the nature and severity of airway infection and inflammation. The identification of purulent secretions through direct visualization via bronchoscopy provides objective evidence of active infection and contributes to the clinical understanding of the patient's respiratory condition, informing subsequent treatment decisions and management strategies.&lt;SEP&gt;Bronchoscopy showed purulent secretions in the patient's respiratory tract.&lt;SEP&gt;Bronchoscopy showed purulent secretions in the patient's airways.&lt;SEP&gt;Bronchoscopy showed purulent secretions in the patient's airways indicating infection.&lt;SEP&gt;The bronchoscopy procedure identified purulent secretions in the patient's airways.</data>
      <data key="d9">airway examination,diagnostic finding,diagnostic observation,diagnostic result,endoscopic finding,endoscopic observation,infection indicator,procedural finding,procedural observation,procedural result,procedure observation,procedure result</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-7cfa77dcd4a2e473aabe4108bc1732c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-348a6f93e1df4665db6794f8f475315a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-92cc2c46c1f49338ed7955ea4238e60f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7f38ad205281fc2b3d3fdc52c5a8b5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74df9a5aaec0ab322e9634e2a357e4ae&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-680b0868e00cfb2dc1ba062d72742486&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b29acdc1599ff32318f1144aaa062a2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b77bea8599e47e5947ec3a7be0ce9b73&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3fa76722cb250ebdc3971241f8d1d7a1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ebdec2fe609dbeb73244f6c370f4d8eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6c7f5f1efa9fe1ad162b412383e280bf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d4f335b1b7bae18006bc038ab4128db1</data>
